title: old-fashioned chicken or beef dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening - slowly mix in milk.
Drop small spoonfuls of dough into boiling chicken or beef broth.
Cook until done.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve
Jell-O
in
boiling
water;
chill.
Blend in chopped
eggs,
celery,
green peppers and onions.
Mix mayonnaise and
corned
beef
together
and add to gelatin mixture. Spread a small amount of mayonnaise in the bottom and sides of a 9
x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Add mixture and refrigerate overnight. Serves 8 to 10.

title: applesauce cake(murphy family recipe)
directions: Warm applesauce (not hot).
Mix soda and salt, set aside. Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Mix spices, 1 cup flour, nuts and raisins.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend all mixtures together and rest of flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
In 1 hour and 15 minutes check cake by using toothpick.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Combine bread crumbs and butter, stirring until well coated. Sprinkle 1/3 of the crumbs in a greased 9-inch baking dish. Drain oysters, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Spoon half the oysters over crumbs. Repeat layers. Combine whipping cream, reserved oyster liquid, sherry and seasonings.
Stir well.
Pour over oysters and sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pina colada wedges
directions: Beat cream
cheese
with
sugar
and
rum until smooth. Fold in 2
cups
of
the whipped topping, pineapple with syrup and 2 cups
of coconut.
Spread in 8-inch layer pan lined with plastic wrap.

title: tofu-watercress salad
directions: Heat oil and garlic to a boil.
Turn off; remove garlic.
Add shoyu, sugar and green onion.
Mix well.
Set aside to cool.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer tofu, onion slices, tomatoes, watercress and salmon or tuna. Pour cooled sauce evenly over layers.
Chill to serve.
May add more shoyu while serving, according to taste.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, oleo and powdered sugar.
Shape into balls. Freeze.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate.

title: meatballs
directions: *Use soup can for measuring.

title: baked french toast
directions: Cube bread and layer half in 9 x 13 pan, which has been sprayed with Pam.
Cut cream cheese into small pieces and scatter across bread.
Cover with remaining bread cubes.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Press down on bread to absorb. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes. Sift powdered sugar over top and serve with additional syrup.

title: sweet potato pie or pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and for pudding, bake in a 9 x 13 pan for 30 to 45 minutes. For pie, bake in an unbaked pie crust for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pistachio pudding cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Roll into walnut size balls and place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Dissolve sugar. Add 2 cups cold water.
Add juices and chill.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green bell pepper together; drain grease.
Mix together soups, beans and Ro-Tel with ground beef and simmer.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate). Arrange potatoes in four layers in 2 quart casserole. Sprinkle the first 3 layers with 1 tablespoon onion, 1 tablespoon flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Sprinkle last layer with remaining onion, salt and pepper. Dot with butter. Pour hot milk over potatoes and bake covered 30 minutes. Bake uncovered 60 to 70 minutes longer. Yields 4 servings.

title: cheese sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in microwave or double boiler.
Add sausage; mix well (with hand).
Add Bisquick; mix well again.
Make into small balls about the size of a walnut.
Bake on cookie sheet in a 350° preheated oven for about 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs and bananas.
Combine milk and vinegar and let stand to make soured milk
Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the soured milk to the sugar mixture.
Begin and end with the flour; mix well.
Stir in nuts, if desired or 1 cup of blueberries.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: grandma mcmurry's corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except franks.
Dry franks and roll in flour.
Dip into batter.
Use a toothpick to retrieve the franks and deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: busy day chicken
directions: Scatter rice on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay pieces of chicken, skin side up on top of rice.
Combine soup, water and onion soup mix.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: kathey's banana pudding
directions: Use large bowl to mix pudding with whole milk as directed on the package.
Next, add the can of sweetened condensed milk to the pudding; stir in good with wire whip if possible.
Last, add the Cool Whip topping.
Stir all together thoroughly.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add beaten eggs and cooking oil.
Blend well.
Beat in carrots and nuts. Pour into a tube pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Peel tomatoes and chop in cubes.
If lots of juice, drain some.
Mash tomatoes.
Put in pot and add lemon juice and Sure-Jell.
Bring to rolling boil.
Add sugar and bring back to rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Turn off heat and put in jars.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Whip egg whites until frothy.
Then add sugar gradually and beat it until stiff peaks form.
Add other ingredients and stir gently.
Drop cookies by spoonfuls onto foil-lined cookie sheets.
Place in oven.
Turn oven off.
Take cookies out next morning.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and flour.
Knead with hands.
Place in pan.
Flatten, then prick with fork.
Sprinkle with colored sugar crystals.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Turn down oven to 300° and bake another 30 minutes, until golden brown on edges.
Turn off oven and leave in oven overnight.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: lemon fruitcake
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: mexican chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine margarine, oil, chocolate and water in saucepan. Heat until chocolate is melted. Combine flour, baking soda, sugar, milk, eggs, cinnamon and vanilla in large bowl, then combine with first mixture. Pour into greased 12 x 18 pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes and prick several times with fork; bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done. Let cool. Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; then scoop out pulp. Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add all-purpose flour, stirring until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, until mix is thick and bubbly. Add potato pulp, salt, pepper, 2 tablespoons onion, 1/2 cup bacon and 1 cup cheese. Cook until thoroughly heated. Stir in sour cream. Add extra milk if necessary for thickness. Add remaining onion, bacon and cheese.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir well.
Cover and chill.
Add mayonnaise, grapes and oranges to chicken mixture.
Toss well. Serve on lettuce and croissant roll.

title: junellen's vegetable lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne according to package directions.
(Separate lasagne and lay out flat on wax paper or aluminum foil to keep pieces from sticking together as they cool.)
Combine Sargento cheese, the vegetables, 2 1/2 cups of the Ricotta and the egg. Place layer of lasagne on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Spread with 1/2 of the cheese mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with lasagne.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Omit salt and baking powder if using self-rising flour.

title: honey whole wheat bread(makes three loaves)
directions: Combine 1/2 cup warm water, yeast and sugar in a small bowl; let sit 5 minutes.
In mixer bowl, combine egg, oil, 2 cups warm water, salt, honey and wheat germ; mix well.
Add yeast mixture. Start blending in the flour until dough becomes too stiff to mix. Add remaining flour by hand, first with a wooden spoon and then by kneading.
Kneading should take 10 to 15 minutes; let raise to double.
Punch down; make loaves.
Grease pans; let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook and drain hamburger; cook and drain noodles.
Mix hamburger, noodles and pizza sauce and place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese and pepperoni.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: plum pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and half fill a mold or a 9 x 5 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Steam for 4 hours.
Cool and chill.
Reheat for serving with butter.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Bake potatoes until tender, then peel and mash them.
(The potatoes can be baked the day before.)
Stir in sugar, orange juice, zest and nutmeg.
Toss the coconut with the sugar and cinnamon.
Press mashed potatoes around each marshmallow, then roll balls in the coconut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Watch carefully for the last few minutes of cooking; the expanded marshmallows can cause the potato balls to burst open.
These are wonderful served with turkey or ham.

title: bean and burger casserole
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Pour off excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well with browned hamburger and onion.
Pour all into casserole dish and bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except onion and soup.
Mix well and form into meatballs.
Brown meatballs with onion in skillet.

title: italian sunset salad
directions: Halve cucumber lengthwise.
Scrape out seed with a spoon. Slice cucumber into half moons.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Toss to mix.
Spoon onto 4 serving plates.
Drizzle vinaigrette on top.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Mix crumbs, 3 Tbsp. sugar and butter together and press firmly into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake crust at 325 degrees for about 10 minutes.
Set baked crust aside to cool.

title: meat loaf barbecue
directions: Combine ground beef, breadcrumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and tomato sauce and pack into a loaf pan.
Combine water, brown sugar, vinegar, hot sauce, mustard and Worcestershire sauce and pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, basting occasionally with sauce and pan juices.
Let cool 20 minutes before serving.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix ingredients together, and place in an ovenproof dish. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and mix until well blended.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Combine flour and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine candy, dates, walnuts and coconut.
Add 1/2 cup of flour mixture and mix well.
In another bowl, cream butter until light. Gradually add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Add remaining flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, blending well.
Stir in candy mixture, mixing well.

title: gob cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for at least 4 minutes.
Line 2 (17 x 11 x 1-inch) pans with waxed paper.
Divide batter between the 2 pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool layers.

title: chess pie
directions: Put starter in refrigerator 5 days or more.
Take and feed with 3/4 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons instant potatoes, 1 cup plain flour and 1 cup warm water.
Mix well and let stand out of refrigerator all day.
This will not rise, only bubble.
Take 1 cup of starter out and make bread; return remaining starter to refrigerator.
You can make bread anytime between feedings.

title: banana raisin bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease six 3-inch crown muffin pan cups.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Boil first four ingredients 1 minute.
Pour into baking dish (approximately 8 x 11-inches) and dot with 3 tablespoons butter. Place in 400° oven while mixing biscuit mix.

title: corn pie
directions: Mix crumbs and butter and press in pie plate.

title: honey dew fudge
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage when dropped in cold water; add vanilla.
Set off stove and let cool to lukewarm. Beat until creamy and smooth; add nuts.
Pour in 9-inch buttered pan to set.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mash ripe peaches.
Add sugar and lemon juice.
Whip the whipping cream slightly.
Put all ingredients in ice cream freezer container and add milk.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix as directed on box.
While still warm, poke holes in cake with a straw. Then pour can of pineapple all over cake.
Mix vanilla pudding, only add 1 1/2 cups of milk. Then fold Cool Whip into pudding.
Can sprinkle coconut all over top of the cake.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and butter until soft ball stage (about 2 minutes).
Take off heat and add vanilla.
Stir and pour over 2 quarts popped corn.
Stir.
Let set just a few minutes to slightly cool.
Butter hands or spray with Pam and shape into balls.

title: millionaire's salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple for 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: terri's jambalaya
directions: Put oil, meats and onion in Dutch oven. Cook on medium-high heat until browned and thoroughly cooked. Add rice, stirring constantly, until rice is fried and brown.
Add seasoning and enough water to cover rice. Cook on high heat until water has boiled away. Cover and cook on low until rice is tender (about 20 minutes). Serves 6.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans and onion in fresh water for 30 minutes.
Dilute soup as directed and combine with other ingredients except the French fried onions.
Add soup mixture to drained beans; place in casserole and bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with French fried onions and brown.
This casserole is great with any kind of meat dish.
Serves 6.

title: scripture cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat well.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Bring oleo, water and cocoa to boil.
Remove from heat and place in bowl.
Add in sugar, flour and salt, then beat in eggs, sour cream and soda.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cake from oven and poke holes into it with a wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over cake.
Heat squeeze bottle of ice cream topping and pour over cake into holes.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with sprinkles or shaved Hershey bar.

title: rhubarb surprise pie
directions: Make regular pie crust dough in a 9-inch pie plate.
Arrange rhubarb in pie shell.
Sprinkle with Jell-O.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle on top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until rhubarb is tender.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add 4 beaten egg yolks (save the whites).
Add poppy seed.
Add or mix in baking soda and sour cream.
Add flour and vanilla.
(Use mixer for all of this.)
Fold in 4 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased loaf pan.
Will make 2 loaves.
Should be baked together.

title: farmhouse dinner
directions: In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain and set aside.

title: oslo cake
directions: Melt oleo in water.
Add flour.
Add eggs, beating as each one is added, until dough sticks together.
Make 2 strips on cooking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water, oil and rum in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes, stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove cake from pan to plate. Prick with cake tester or fork, and drizzle glaze over top and sides.
Allow cake to absorb glaze.
Repeat until all glaze is used.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cheese, bacon, and onion.
Set aside.
Mix salad dressing, vinegar, and sugar until well blended.
Add mixtures together and serve!

title: cake that won't last
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour, oil, soda, salt, vanilla and cinnamon. Fold in bananas, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave rice
directions: Measure rice, salt and oleo into 2-quart casserole (1 round preferred).
Stir in hot water.
Cover.
Microwave at High 5 minutes then change to 50% power for 11 to 15 minutes.
Stir, then let stand, covered, 2 to 4 minutes.

title: fish en croute
directions: Prepare filling by beating softened cheeses with egg and seasonings.
Roll out puff pastry in a cookie sheet up to the edges.
Lay half of perch fillets in center. Put filling on top. Lay the rest of the perch over filling.
Bring pastry up around fish and pinch closed.
Trim extra and use to "decorate" like a fish.
Use water to attach scales, fins, tail.

title: ham pickle pinwheels
directions: Place cream cheese, salami and horseradish in a blender or food processor; cover and process until smooth.
Spread over ham slices. Remove stems and ends of okra pickles.
Place two or three okra pickles or one dill pickle down the center of each ham slice.
Roll up tightly and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and sausage.
Drain fat.
Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook until cheese melts.
Serve over chips.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until thick. Add corn syrup, nuts and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell. Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Spread meat flat; mix remaining ingredients except oil and sauce.
Put a bit of stuffing in the center of each piece of meat. Roll up and secure with wooden toothpicks or cotton thread.
Heat oil; saute each roll-up until brown.
Place roll-ups in crock-pot; add sauce.
Cook on low for 4 hours or until meat is tender. Remove toothpicks.
Serve over rice or hot buttered noodles.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: With electric mixer, beat butter, peanut butter and sugar. Add salt and soda. Continue mixing and add eggs. Gradually add flour and vanilla. Spoon onto greased
cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fluffy icing
directions: Bring to a rolling boil. Beat 3 egg whites stiff. Pour syrup over egg whites. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat until cooled.

title: pasta and peas italian
directions: One hour before:
Combine all ingredients except peas and pasta.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
(Combined refrigerated ingredients are uncooked.)
Cook pasta and prepare peas according to package. Combine cooked pasta and peas; toss with refrigerated mixture. Serve warm or cold.
(Add more oil and water if a more liquid base is desired.)

title: apple squares
directions: Mix egg, milk, sugar and vanilla, then add flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add apple pieces, raisins and nuts.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in an 8-inch square pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 325° oven.
Makes one pie.

title: yeast bread
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and combine with milk, eggs, sugar, salt and yeast that has dissolved in warm water.
Using electric mixer, beat in 2 cups flour, stir in remaining flour by hand. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, on a floured board, roll out dough.
Knead and place in a well-greased loaf pan or muffin pan for rolls.
Let rise now for 2 hours.
Brush tops with remaining stick of butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix together.
Roll out and let dry for approximately 1/2 hour.
Roll up and cut.
Spread strips to dry.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk; bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove; stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme and blend.
Add nuts.
Put in buttered dish. Cool and cut.

title: ione's apple crumble-crust pie
directions: Sweeten apples as for pie; place in a large pie pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg with a fork; sprinkle on top of apples.
Over this pour 1/3 cup melted shortening or salad oil. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake until apples are done and crust is brown.

title: savory musetti (scrambled lasagna)
directions: While noodles are hot, add the sour cream, cream cheese and Velveeta.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Layer meat mixture, noodle mixture and grated cheese in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mike's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Use sauce to baste chicken or lamb when grilling.
I find it is better to let sauce simmer for about 30 minutes before using.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Put in pie crust and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn oven temperature down to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until done.

title: rhubarb-raspberry pie
directions: Mix and place in crust.
Top with crust.
Score top.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle top with sugar before cooking.
Eat plain or with ice cream.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix together and let stand for awhile to form juice.
Bring to a boil and cook 15 minutes or until rhubarb is done.
Turn to low heat and add 3 ounce package of strawberry or raspberry gelatin.
Stir to dissolve.
Pour in warm sterilized jars and seal.
Store in cool place.

title: chicken and potato sauté
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Add onion and garlic, cook about 5 minutes.
In a small bowl combine flour and seasonings.
Stir in broth until smooth; pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add potatoes and water; heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Drop from spoon.
Cook about 5 or 10 minutes.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Mix together soups, milk and rice and pour mixture in pan.
Top with chicken breasts and sprinkle dry soup mix over top.
Cover with foil and bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Do not peek!

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown ground beef.
Make sauce of ground beef, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, oregano, egg, salt, pepper and Ragu.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut
cabbage
into chunks, cook and drain. Melt 1 stick butter;
put milk and dry ingredients in blender and mix well. Add to
butter
and stir until blended.
Add chunks of cheese and melt
cheese.
Pour
mixture
over cabbage.
Melt another stick of butter and tear 4 slices of bread into crumbs; add to butter
and put
on
top
of
casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no salt seasoning
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Makes 1/4 cup of seasoning. You can make as much as you like and store in airtight container.

title: quail hunter's bounty
directions: Place quail breast in pan of water and boil for 10 minutes. Drain and arrange breasts in baking dish.
Make gravy from one can of cream of mushroom soup, 1/2 cup water and diced apple.
In a small saucepan, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat when it begins to boil.
Pour over quail breasts. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lentil-barley stew
directions: Saute in a large pan:
margarine, onion and celery.
Add water and lentils, cook 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes, barley, salt, pepper, rosemary and garlic salt; simmer 45 to 60 minutes, until barley is tender.
Add carrots.
Cook five minutes and serve.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable and cheese sandwiches
directions: Stir together drained cottage cheese, shredded carrots, chopped green pepper or celery and chives in a small bowl.
Stir in yogurt.
Spread bread slices with mustard.
Top with spinach leaves.
Spoon cottage cheese mixture onto bread slices.
Top with tomato slices. Makes 4 servings.

title: ellen's hot potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together except crumbs and paprika.
Pack into casserole.
Sprinkle top with crumbs and paprika.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: crunchy christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients. Add nuts and other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: old country tomato bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and set aside.
Cream shortening, sugar and salt until smooth.
Add tomato juice and mix well.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add to yeast, stir well.
Gradually add half the flour, beating well.
Add the remainder of the flour, mix well.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board and knead 5 minutes.
Place into greased bowl.
Cover with clean cloth, let rise in warm place for 2 hours.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board.
Shape into 1 large or 2 small loaves.
Place in greased loaf pan and brush top with melted butter.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Then lower heat and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over medium heat in a large pot to 210° on thermometer.
Add oleo and pecans.
Cook over medium heat to 230°.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Stir until no gloss shows and is cooled.
Add quickly, by spoonful, to wax paper, on work surface.

title: rhubarb-strawberry jam
directions: Let rhubarb and sugar stand overnight in refrigerator.
Then boil 20 minutes (no more).
Take off heat and add Jell-O.
Stir just to dissolve, then pour into jelly jars.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add dry ingredients, milk and vanilla. Beat well. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 50 minutes. Remove from pan and cover with glaze while cake is still hot.

title: maw-maw's cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Bake in small amounts (approximately 1/2 teaspoon) on ungreased baking sheet for about 20 minutes at 300° until lightly browned.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake and set aside.
Punch holes in cake and pour mixture of pineapple and sugar on top.
Mix pudding and pour on top of pineapple topping.
Before serving, add sliced bananas on top of pudding.
Spread Cool Whip on top of bananas.
Sprinkle with pecans.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil.
Heat in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until softened.
For sauce, in a saucepan, cook onion, garlic, coriander and pepper in margarine or butter until onion is tender. Stir flour into sour cream; add onion mixture.
Stir in broth and chili peppers all at once.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the cheese.

title: sour cream sugared nuts
directions: Mix sour cream and sugar.
Heat to 223°, stirring constantly. Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir rapidly until mixture has coated nuts and sugared.
Spread on trays and separate.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Will keep several months.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Brown meat. Add onion. Cook until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer over low heat 30 minutes.
Spoon over toasted buns.

title: french breakfast muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add milk, egg and 1/3 cup butter; put in greased and floured small muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Check, as it doesn't take long at all in the small tins.
Remove immediately.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix together and melt cheese over low heat.
Serve with corn chips.

title: asparagus with tangy sauce
directions: Cook asparagus in boiling water until tender; drain.
While asparagus is cooking, make the sauce by combining sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice and mustard in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until thoroughly heated.
Pour sauce over hot asparagus or serve separately in bowl and let everyone help themselves.
Garnish with chopped pimento if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Place sliced tomatoes in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cover with green onions. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Sprinkle generously with lemon pepper.
Top with grated cheese and crushed crackers. Dot with margarine.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 45 minutes. Uncover and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: blueberry surprise pie
directions: Bake pie crust according to directions and let cool.
Cream softened cream cheese and sugar.
Layer sliced bananas, cream cheese mixture and pie filling in pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip. Chill well.

title: six layer salad
directions: Layer in (8 x 10 inch) pan:

title: wheat squares
directions: In
medium
mixing
bowl mix flours, wheat germ, sugar, salt and
soda
well.
Stir
in
water and butter until smooth dough forms.
Divide
in half; cover and let stand at least 10 minutes. Place
half
the dough on lightly oiled 17 x 14-inch baking sheet; flatten into 4-inch square.
Roll out on baking sheet to
1/2 x 13 1/2-inch rectangle.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Prick all
over
with
fork;
brush
with
water. Sprinkle with
coarse salt
or
table salt to taste.
Bake in middle of
preheated
400° oven
for
7 to 8 minutes or until crisp but
not
overbrowned. Remove to racks to cool.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Makes 198. Squares shrink to just over 1-inch after baking.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add buttermilk until consistency that holds its shape but is not dry.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot deep fat and fry until brown.

title: crab mold
directions: Toss crab, celery and onion in a bowl.
Warm soup; add cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Add mayonnaise, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce.

title: denver sandwiches
directions: Fry bacon.
Combine eggs with remaining ingredients and blend well.
Add to bacon and cook.
Serve on or off bread.

title: french silk pie
directions: Blend butter until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually.
Mix well. Melt chocolate with pinch of salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat 5 minutes after each egg.
Pour into baked pie shell. Spread with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts.
Chill 3 hours before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until done.
Boil broccoli in salted water until tender.
Tear chicken into bite size pieces and layer bottom of casserole dish and top with a layer of broccoli; spread 1/2 can of soup over top.
Add dash of curry powder.
Top with half of cheese.
Repeat layers (do not repeat curry powder). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese dip(power setting medium, probe 130~)
directions: Drain clams.
Place all ingredients in a 1-quart casserole. Stir well; insert probe.
If you do not have a probe, the cooking time will be about 6 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Mix in a large bowl cherries, dates and pecans.
Sift over that the sugar, flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Beat 4 eggs until foamy, add 1 teaspoon vanilla and pour over mixture. Mix well.
Grease bottom of tube cake pan, put a paper over bottom and grease again.
Pack dough into pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until foamy. Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
In separate bowl, mix flour, soda, salt, baking powder, spices, fruit and nuts until blended. Stir gently into zucchini mixture just until blended.
Spoon equally into 2 greased and flour dusted loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread pulls away from the side of the pans. Cool in pans for 10 minutes.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and form into a loaf.
Add water to remainder of soup in can and pour over loaf.
Bake about 1-1/2 hours at 325-350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Add raisins that have been floured first to keep from sinking to the bottom of pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
You may substitute bananas for the zucchini.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Layer in a clear, straight-sided bowl (a trifle bowl works well) all ingredients, in any order, with the following exceptions:

title: tacos
directions: Brown the ground beef until crumbly; drain the fat.
Add the taco seasoning and the water; blend well.
Bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon the meat filling into the taco shells.
Top with shredded lettuce, grated Cheddar cheese and chopped onions and tomatoes.

title: caramel fudge
directions: In a separate pot, place 1/2 cup sugar and cook until it becomes medium brown.

title: country chicken with creamy gravy
directions: Place cereal, paprika, poultry seasoning, thyme, salt and pepper in a shallow dish, stirring well to combine.
Pour Egg Beaters in a shallow bowl or dish.
Dip chicken breast halves in Egg Beaters to coat.
Dredge in cereal mixture.
Place coated chicken in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish with thickest portions towards outside of dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave at High for 12 minutes or until chicken is done.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn every 4 minutes.
You can also bake chicken in the oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Spoon Creamy Gravy evenly over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Slice strawberries into baked crust.
Cook water, sugar and cornstarch over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Continue to cook over low heat for 2 minutes. Remove from heat; add strawberry gelatin.
Stir until dissolved; pour over strawberries.
Chill until set.
Top with whipped cream.

title: mrs. mendelbright's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Line baking sheets with foil.
Wash and remove the stems from the mushrooms.
Chop and reserve 1/2 cup of the stems.
Brush the caps with the butter and place on the trays.
In a medium bowl, combine the Parmesan, mushroom stems, garlic salt and cream cheese, blending well.
Fill the caps with the mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
May be frozen.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Makes 80 stuffed mushrooms.

title: venison
directions: Mix the vinegar and soy sauce together in a shallow baking dish.
Dip both sides of the meat in it and let it marinate overnight in the refrigerator, covered.
Then follow any beef recipe.
If pan-frying, steaks will need a bit more time than three minutes to cook.
If the steaks are 1-inch thick, fry over high heat for 3 minutes on each side.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into loaf in baking pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 2 quart baking dish, place chicken and vegetables.
Stir together soup, chicken broth and pepper to taste.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Combine flour, milk and butter. Stir until smooth.
Pour this over top.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Let cool about 10 minutes before serving.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Shape into balls. Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no-fat eggs
directions: Combine ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Stir or whisk until smooth.
Keep in a closed container.
Use 1/4 cup to equal 1 egg. This freezes well or will keep for a week in the refrigerator. Use in place of whole eggs in any recipe calling for a beaten egg.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese with confectioners sugar.
Add peanut butter.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: confetti corn salad
directions: Toss corn, celery, pimiento, green pepper and onion lightly. Mix together cider vinegar, salad oil, sugar, salt and pepper. Pour over vegetables.
Marinate several hours in refrigerator.

title: scalloped corn and cheese
directions: Beat eggs in medium casserole dish.
In small saucepan, heat corn and milk.
Stir mixture into egg; add salt, bread and cheese. Mix well.
Bake at 325° uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: fig preserves
directions: Mix and let set 1/2 day until sugar melts. Put into large pot. Cook until juice is thick and water is cooked out. Pour into jars and seal.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, stir sugar and syrup together.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla, blending well.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Peanuts will be slightly brown and syrup very hot.
Add baking soda; gently stir until light and fluffy. Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1/2 to 1 hour, then break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: egg custard
directions: Let milk and butter come to boil.
Pour into well-beaten sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well as you pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Turn oven down to 250°.
Bake until done.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and bring to a soft boil. Remove from heat and add the oleo and vanilla.
Beat until slightly thickened.
Add pecans.
Beat about 1 minute and drop on wax paper.

title: shrimp oriental
directions: Bring water, soy sauce, sherry and onion to boil in skillet; stir in rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add shrimp, red pepper, pea pods and ginger.
Stir.
Cover and remove from heat. Let stand until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.

title: chicken wings canton
directions: Cut wings in half; discard tips, or save for use in chicken broth.
Rinse; pat dry with paper towels.
Pour soy sauce into shallow bowl; set aside.
In another shallow bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Dip chicken in soy sauce; roll in seasoned crumbs, coating evenly.
Arrange chicken wings, skin side up, in spoke pattern in 9-inch round glass pie plate, placing thickest portions toward outside of plate.
Cover with paper towels.
Cook on High 7 minutes.
Rotate dish one-quarter turn.
Cook on High 5 to 7 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Serve hot.

title: dilled snacks
directions: Toss all together.
Lay out on paper towels to air dry for 30 to 60 minutes.
Will keep for a long time if stored in airtight containers.

title: chicken crepes
directions: Mix eggs, salt and milk in blender.
Add flour and mix for another 10 to 15 seconds.
(Overmixing will cause bubbles to form in the batter.)
Pour batter on crepe maker or in flat pan to make crepes for filling.

title: phyllo chicken
directions: Brush sides and bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with some of the melted butter.
Place one sheet of phyllo in bottom of dish; brush with butter.
Repeat with 5 more sheets of phyllo. (Keep remaining phyllo dough covered with waxed paper to avoid drying out.)
In a bowl, combine chicken, bacon, broccoli and cheese; spread evenly over phyllo in baking dish.

title: 20 minute apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium and cook 20 minutes, stirring constantly. Put in hot jars and seal.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook syrup mixture until a hard ball forms in cold water. Beat eggs until they form a peak.
Add nuts, cherries or coconut.

title: frozen salad
directions: Fold together; pour into a Pyrex dish, 6 x 10 x 2-inches and freeze.

title: broiled salmon steaks with herb sauce
directions: Combine butter or margarine, wine, parsley, herbs and garlic; heat slowly until fat is melted.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Sprinkle steaks with salt.
Place fish on a well-greased broiler pan (or line pan with greased foil); brush with sauce.
Broil about 3 inches from heat source, 4 to 6 minutes.
Turn carefully; brush with sauce.
Broil about 3 inches from heat source, 4 to 6 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Baste steaks with sauce several times while broiling.
Makes 6 servings.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Roll into balls and press down lightly with sugared glass on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes until lightly browned.

title: best ever fruit compote
directions: Mix all together in a large pan.
Simmer very gently for 45 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower and onion.
Add remaining ingredients; toss until well coated.

title: poppa's chili
directions: Pour tomato soup and 1 can water into large pot.
Brown meat; salt and pepper to taste.
Add meat to soup and let simmer.
Cut onion, celery and pepper into small pieces and add to soup and meat.
Add ketchup and mustard.
Stir well and simmer about 2 hours.
Drain beans well and add to mixture.
Simmer about 30 minutes and enjoy.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheesecake(low-fat)
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of 7-inch spring-form pan; set aside.
In food processor, add cream cheese and next 7 ingredients and mix until smooth.
Add egg to food processor and mix until blended.
Fold in chocolate morsels.

title: banana shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: smoked oyster spread
directions: Finely chop oysters, celery and onions.
Combine first 6 ingredients and mix with cheese.
Add liquid from can of oysters. Refrigerate 2 1/2 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: spinach casserole(serves 6)
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Drain. Cook spinach; drain. Beat egg with milk and salt. Stir in the spinach, bacon, bread crumbs, minced onion and 1/2 cup cheese. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with additional cheese and paprika. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: icing in the cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, water and eggs. Beat as directions on box instruct.
Add frosting and pecans.
Beat on low until folded in. Bake in well-greased and floured Bundt pan on top rack of oven. Bake at 350° approximately 55 to 60 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes before removing from pan onto wire rack to finish cooling.

title: peanut butter streusel pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Blend peanut butter with confectioners sugar until mealy.
Sprinkle 2/3 of mixture over baked pe shell (save remaining for top of meringue).
Combine 1/2 cup sugar (save half for meringue), flour and salt.
Stir in scalded milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickens.
Stir in a few tablespoons of filling into beaten egg yolks.
Put back into mixture.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Make meringue. Put onto pie.
Sprinkle with remaining confectioners sugar/peanut butter mixture. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: orange meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and hot water in a saucepan.
Gradually stir in orange juice.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Slowly stir half of mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks, then beat into rest of mixture in saucepot.
Boil 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in butter, lemon juice and rind.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: diet banana split cake
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs; press down in bottom of pan.
Add layer of bananas, then prepared pudding (made according to box), layer of pineapple, layer of pudding, layer of bananas, nuts and then Cool Whip.
Garnish with pecans and cherries.

title: beef stew
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in casserole or heavy stew pot.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour over casserole and bake at 200° for 4 hours, covered.

title: cucumber cooly
directions: Toss all ingredients together and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with mixer, then add grapes.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Cut steak into pieces of your choice.
Dip into egg and then into flour.
Place in about 2 inches of hot grease.
Let fry until golden brown.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until the Jell-O begins to thicken and strawberries are broken apart.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes.
Place half of cake pieces in cake pan or large glass bowl.
Pour half of Jell-O mixture over cake pieces.
Add the rest of the cake pieces and Jell-O mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Frost with Dream Whip or Cool Whip and top with whole strawberries.

title: ham dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut ham steaks in half.
Make 6 packets from heavy-duty foil.
Put on ham slice:
mustard, sprinkle of brown sugar, pear halves and sweet potato halves.
Dot with butter.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water. Stir to dissolve and add cranberry sauce. Add celery, apples and nuts. Chill until firm.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix together ketchup, brown sugar, chili sauce and horseradish sauce.
Put beans in a 3-quart dish; pour mixture evenly over top. Sprinkle onions on top.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours, covered.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla at medium speed until fluffy. Fold in whipped cream. Serve with fruit.

title: sweet potato pudding pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° in oven until firm to the touch.

title: strawberry sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square or 9-inch round cake pan.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Add Crisco, sugar and salt.
Pour boiling water over mixture. Blend and cool.
Add eggs.
Put yeast cakes in cold water for 5 minutes.
Refrigerate for 4 hours after cutting out.
Then let rise for 3 hours. Keeps for 10 days.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix baking soda and buttermilk; mix all other ingredients, then add milk.
Cook on grill or in skillet.

title: chicken pillows
directions: Rub each chicken breast with garlic, salt and pepper.
Place slice of ham and slice of cheese on each breast.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Roll, starting at broader end.
Secure with toothpick and place in lightly greased dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Heat sherry and butter together, pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: childrens fun time cookie
directions: These cookies you squeeze, smash or beat. The more you squeeze, smash or beat, the better the cookie.

title: healthy burritos
directions: Mix refried beans, salsa and green chiles in saucepan.
Cook at medium heat.
Meanwhile, prepare lettuce, tomatoes, onion and bell peppers.
Heat tortillas in oven 5 minutes at 325°.
Place one large spoonful bean mixture onto center of tortillas.
Top with lettuce, tomato, onion, peppers and cheese to taste.
Roll up tortilla and enjoy.
This makes a delicious low-fat meal.

title: red cucumber rings
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime and 1 gallon water for 24 hours; drain and rinse.
Cover with ice water for 3 hours; drain.
Mix 2 cups vinegar, red food coloring and alum with water to cover.
Simmer for 2 hours; drain.
Mix 2 cups vinegar, 2 cups water, sugar, cinnamon sticks and red hot candy.
Pour over rings and let stand for 24 hours.
Drain and save liquid.
Bring liquid to a boil. Place pickle rings in jar.
Pour boiling syrup over pickles and seal.

title: easy chicken stroganoff
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat in 1 tablespoon of margarine, cook half of the chicken until browned.
Remove. Repeat with remaining chicken.
Reduce heat to medium.
In same skillet, cook mushrooms and onion until tender and liquid is evaporated.
Stir often.
Add gravy and sour cream.
Return chicken to skillet.
Hat through, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley.

title: steak and sweetbread kabobs
directions: In a large saucepan, squeeze lemons and salt. Combine sweetbreads with 1 quart of water to pan.
Allow lemon juice and salt to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Saute turkey and bacon.
Drain. Cut into 1-inch cubes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs in half lengthwise.
Take out yolk; mash with fork.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping lightly.
Arrange on a large serving plate.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, then roll out and cut. Place on cookie sheet. Mixture will be soft. You may set in refrigerator until cool. Will be easier to work with. Roll lightly and cut. Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: burnt cream
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat cream over low until bubbles form around edge of pan.
Beat egg yolks and sugar together until thick, about 3 minutes.
Gradually beat cream into egg yolks. Stir in vanilla and pour into six 6-ounce custard cups.
Place in baking pan that has about 1/2 inch of water in the bottom.
Bake until set, about 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Place under broiler and cook until topping is medium brown.
Chill before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: peanut butter bonbon balls
directions: In a saucepan melt peanut butter and butter.
In a large bowl combine powdered sugar and cereal.
Pour peanut butter mixture over cereal mixture, blend together with hands.
Form into 1/2 inch balls.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate, place on waxed paper lined baking sheet, then chill.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Bring butter, sugar, milk and cocoa to a boil.
Add vanilla and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Let melt, then add quick oats. Stir well, then drop by teaspoon on waxed paper. Allow cookies to harden.
Then remove from waxed paper.

title: orange pull-a-parts
directions: Arrange biscuits in greased Bundt pan.
Dissolve margarine, sugar and juice together; pour over biscuits while sauce is still hot.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, then tip upside down on a large plate.
Serve hot or cold.
Especially great for breakfast.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add cornstarch, cocoa and melted margarine.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into two unbaked crusts and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: date bars
directions: Boil dates, sugar and water . Mix well until all dates are blended until smooth.
Pour mixture over layer of crumbs in pan and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: nutty banana bread
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Stir in bananas.
Combine flour and remaining ingredients; add to creamed mixture, mixing just until blended.
Spoon batter into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden toothpick comes out clean.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: In 1-quart jar, combine all ingredients, except onion and mushrooms.
Shake until well blended.
Add onions and mushrooms. Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Remove mushrooms.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: quick pie crust
directions: Bring to a boil first 3 ingredients.
Add flour, put it in a pie plate and form crust.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine 1/2 cup milk with soup.
Mix into vegetables with 1/2 can onions and 1/2 cup cheese.
Sprinkle with pepper to taste. Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Test vegetables to see if done, then top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes more.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter, butter, sugars and eggs.
Sift flour with soda and add all remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Yield: 7 dozen.

title: old-fashioned cabbage rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend meat with egg, milk and bread crumbs. Stir in salt, molasses, ginger, nutmeg, allspice and onion.
Mix well.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat 1 cup pear juice and dissolve Jell-O in juice.
While it cools, mash pears and cream cheese together, then combine with Jell-O.
Let set until slightly thickened. Add whipped cream and put in refrigerator to jell.

title: crab cakes
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender and remove from heat.
In a bowl, mix crabmeat, onion and pepper mixture, and next 9 ingredients.
Mix well and shape into patties. Coat with additional breadcrumbs.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 3 ingredients.
Fold in cheese and broccoli.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour, top with additional cheese.

title: vegetable clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Add clam liquid, water, tomatoes and tomato sauce to onion and bacon.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery and seasonings.
Simmer on low heat until potatoes and carrots are tender.
Add clams, peas and corn.
Heat to boiling.
Serves 4.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining ingredients together.
Add to sugar and egg mixture and mix well.
Stir in 1 cup M&M's.
Reserve remaining candies for decorations.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: starr's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, syrup, melted butter and vanilla extract.
Mix well.
Add pecans, folding pecans into mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until firm.
Shake pie gently to check firmness.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and serve with french bread cubes.

title: beef casserole
directions: Combine meat, gravy and vegetables.
Pour in casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: drain declogger
directions: Pour baking soda into drain.
Follow with vinegar.
Close drain tightly until fizzing stops.
Flush with pot of boiling water.

title: sliced cookies
directions: Beat eggs and then put in sugar.
Add oil.
Add flour mixed with baking powder.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon to form loaf on each side of pans.
Cook at 375° until they are brown.
Slice and toast.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate for several hours before serving. Serve with fresh raw vegetables (carrots, broccoli, celery, cauliflower, radishes, etc.) or chips and crackers.

title: cheese-sausage corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute onion and pepper in butter until tender, about 5 minutes.
Brown sausage according to package directions; drain.

title: enchilada lasagna
directions: In 9-inch round casserole dish, pour a little enchilada sauce. Place 3 tortillas and add a little sauce.
Add 1/2 hamburg mixture and 1/2 onion.
Add some shredded cheese.
Repeat, layering tortillas, sauce, hamburg, onion and cheese, then finish with tortillas and sauce, then rest of cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes, then uncovered about 15 minutes.
Let stand before serving.
Serve with salsa, sour cream, back olives, chopped tomatoes, lettuce or whatever you like.
Serves 4.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix juices into punch bowl.
Add sherbet and ginger ale before guests start arriving.

title: honey mustard
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with ham or as a sandwich spread.
Yield: 3/4 cup.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar; blend.
Add flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add apples, pecans and vanilla.
Bake at 350° in large tube pan for 1 hour.
Ice with Caramel Glaze.

title: honey and garlic chicken wings
directions: Disjoint wings and clip wing tips.
Place in pan and baste with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baked ziti
directions: Brown ground beef with Ro-Tel and garlic salt.	Stir in Ragu sauce.
Pour over cooked pasta that has been placed in baking dish.
Stir so that pasta is covered in sauce.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake until cheese has melted.

title: altitude instant potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed on package. For extra richness, use evaporated milk (the same amount as the required liquid in potato preparation).

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together; save some cheese for topping.
Place mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers or French bread.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Put peaches in 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar over peaches.
Mix cake as usual but instead of water use peach juice.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Good served with ice cream.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak the oats and sour milk for 1/2 hour.
Cream together the Crisco, brown sugar and eggs.
Add the flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add the oatmeal mixture.
Stir just to blend. Fill paper lined muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Makes 24.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Fry hamburger meat with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain hamburger meat.
Put meat in bottom of casserole dish, then add green beans.
Cover with cream of chicken soup and then spread Tater Tots on top (one layer only).
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: risotto with asparagus and pine nuts
directions: Snap off tough ends of asparagus.
Remove scales from stalks with a knife or vegetable peeler, if desired.
Cut off asparagus tips; set aside.
Thinly slice stems; set aside.
Saute shallot in butter in a large skillet over medium heat until tender; add rice. Stir in wine; cook, stirring constantly until liquid cooks down.

title: marinated shark steaks
directions: Combine lemon, garlic, Italian dressing, salt and pepper.
Put shark steaks in mixture and let stand at least one hour.
Grill on outdoor grill or bake in foil with pat of butter on each steak.

title: chicken artichoke salad
directions: Bake chicken with usual seasonings. Cool and dice.
Marinate artichokes in Italian dressing overnight. Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions; then cool. Mix all ingredients
after draining artichokes (save marinade to add to salad, if needed, for moisture).
Taste and adjust for preferred moisture.
Add more dressing, if needed. Top with nuts and garnish with parsley.

title: eddie's beet pickles
directions: Cook and skin enough beets to make 4 pints.
Cover whole or sliced beets with sugar, water and vinegar; simmer 20 minutes. Add spices the last 10 minutes.

title: fig berry preserves
directions: Thoroughly mix figs, gelatin and sugar in a large saucepan. Bring to boil over medium heat and continue boiling for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour quickly into glasses.
Cover at once with 1/8 inch of hot paraffin.

title: boston clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes with enough water to cover.
Cook onion at same time.
Stir occasionally so they do not stick.
By the time they are soft, most of liquid disappears.
Add the clams and clam juice.
Shake about a cup of water with 3 or 4 tablespoons flour in a jar to mix for thickening.
Add flour and water (strain if lumpy) to clams and potatoes.
Add enough milk to make chowder your desired consistency.
If chowder is too thin, add more flour and water mixture.
Heat only to boiling.
Add cooked, diced bacon and seasonings.
Remove from heat and let stand covered for about 5 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: italian beef
directions: In a large crock-pot, place roast, entire jar of peppers (juice too), cut up onion and packet of au jus seasoning. Cook all day on high. When roast is tender, tear apart and serve on hoagie buns with Swiss cheese.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except cornstarch in 3-quart saucepan. Bring to boil.
Turn heat down to simmer.
Stirring occasionally, cook for 20 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in small amount of water. Add to other ingredients.

title: old fashioned cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread according to directions. Let cool and crumble. Mix all ingredients together and chill at least 2 hours for flavors to blend.

title: pumpkin mincemeat bread
directions: Sift together flour, white sugar, spice(s), soda and salt.
Mix in brown sugar.
Make a well in the center.
Add eggs, water, oil and pumpkin.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer until ingredients are blended.
Then beat at medium speed about 3 minutes.
Stir in mincemeat and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° until done when tested with toothpick.
You may use loaf pans or coffee cans or soup cans.
The batter will fit into:

four 1 pound coffee cans and bake 50 to 60 minutes; three medium size loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches) and bake 55 to 65 minutes; two large loaf pans (9 1/2 x 5 1/2 x 2 3/4-inches) and bake 60 to 70 minutes or eight soup cans (fill half or 2/3 full and then place on baking sheet) and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: In medium bowl, with fork, mix mayonnaise, horseradish, milk, salt, onion and dill seed until well blended.
Add cabbage and carrots and toss until well blended.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts and raisins.
Stir nuts and raisins in after you have mixed other ingredients.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: grandma barb's dumplings
directions: In a bowl, sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add 1/2 cup milk. Mix until forms a soft dough.
Blend in melted shortening. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto boiling soup.
Cover tightly and steam without lifting cover for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: emergency recipe for cranberry sauce
directions: Marinate red cherries in Port wine to cover.
Melt the currant jelly.
Add unflavored gelatin.
Soften in 1/4 cup Port wine. Heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Set remaining wine aside.
Throw in the lemon with a dash of hope.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Beat together the margarine, sugar and eggs, then add applesauce and buttermilk.
In another bowl, blend the flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Add to first mixture and blend.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes a delicious cake, also.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: NOTE:
Do not use Reduced Fat Butter, will cause chocolate to clump and will not coat evenly.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Add egg and a little milk.
Mix to a smooth batter.
Beat for 5 minutes until air bubbles appear. Then add the remaining milk slowly.
Leave to stand before using. Heat drippings in a tin (8 x 10-inch) or small muffin tins.
Pour the batter into pan.
Bake on top rack for 30 minutes at 425°. Muffin tins should bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: skillet zucchini
directions: Pan-fry in large skillet sausage or chuck for 15 minutes. Drain off fat.
Add onions, zucchini and garlic powder.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, basil, oregano and salt.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add cheese.
Simmer until it melts.
May be served over rice, but it is very good plain.

title: squash
directions: Cut squash in rounds.
Cook about 5 minutes in salted water. Drain.
In a skillet add oil, onion, salt, pepper and squash.
Fry until it starts to brown.

title: reese's cup tarts
directions: Cream butters and sugars thoroughly.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Take rounded teaspoonfuls of dough and place in greased miniature muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cookie puffs up and is barely done.
Remove from oven and immediately push a peanut butter cup into each cookie.
The cookies will deflate and form a tart shell around the peanut butter cup.
Let cool in pan, then refrigerate until shine leaves the chocolate. Lift out tarts gently with tip of sharp knife.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: oklahoma caviar
directions: Open all cans and dump in a strainer to drain. Chop the green onion and red onion. Put all ingredients in a bowl; mix well. Pour Zesty Italian dressing in and marinate overnight. Before serving, stick in strainer and drain.

title: e z fudge
directions: In a large bowl, put the nuts, melted butter, vanilla and chocolate chips.
In a heavy saucepan, put the evaporated milk, sugar and marshmallows; boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over ingredients in bowl; mix until chips dissolve.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch glass dish and cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: This is a fine pie to serve with Thanksgiving dinner if you're not locked into the traditional pumpkin pie. Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; stir to combine.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Beat butter until creamy and gradually add sugars, beating until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla, eggs and chocolate.
Add oats mixture; blend well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes. Remove from pan; cool thoroughly.
Add icing.

title: chili burger supper
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add soups and macaroni.
Heat and stir until bubbly.
Halve cheese slices; overlap slices over macaroni mixture.
Cover until cheese melts. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fried corn on the cob
directions: Prepare 8 young fresh ears of corn (cleaned, washed and dried). Heat oil in deep fryer. Drop fresh, raw corn in oil. Cook 2 to 3 minutes until light brown. Lightly salt and put on margarine, if you wish.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix oats and buttermilk in large bowl.
Let sit a while (a few minutes okay or overnight in refrigerator).
Beat in eggs and butter.
Add raisins, if used.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat a lightly greased frying pan over moderate heat.
If batter is too thick, you can add up to 3 tablespoons more buttermilk.
Cook pancakes until a few bubbles appear.
Turn to brown other side. Makes about 18 pancakes.

title: eggnog fudge
directions: Butter bottom and sides of an 8 x 4 x 2-inch pan and set aside.
Butter the sides of a heavy, 2-quart saucepan.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Thaw and raise dough.
May substitute dough made in breadmaker.
Melt margarine with seasonings.
Save 2 tablespoons and spread remaining mixture on dough.
Arrange pepperoni on buttered dough.
Cover with cheese.
Roll as a jelly roll.
Seal edges by pinching.
Place on cookie sheet with sealed edge down. Brush with reserved mixture.
Let rise for 15 minutes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1/2 hour.
Brush with remaining mixture.

title: american oriental stir-fry
directions: In bowl, mix cornstarch and chicken broth until smooth. Stir in soy sauce, honey and pepper.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Use whisk to beat eggs into noodles until foamy.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Butter pan and pour mixture into it, placing several pieces of butter on top.
Can also sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes (depending on stove) or until sides and top brown.
Can also be frozen and baked at later time.
Can be served with sour cream.

title: jumbo bran muffins
directions: Mix
oil, melted margarine, buttermilk, eggs, honey and molasses.
Add Grape-Nuts and
bran.
Mix in separate bowl the flour, soda, baking powder, brown sugar and salt.
Make a well in middle of dry ingredients
and
add wet.
Stir until barely mixed. Bake at 400° for
20 to 25 minutes.
These are wonderful and sweet.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, stir together brown sugar, flour and eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie crust.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes (thawed), sour cream, onions, soup and 1 cup cheese.
Place in casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove.
Add crushed corn flakes mixed with remaining 1/2 cup cheese over top. Dribble with melted oleo.
Return to oven.
Bake another 15 to 20 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Let pickles stand in salt water overnight.
In morning, drain pickles from salt water.
Add rest of ingredients to pickles. Heat well but do not boil.
Seal in cans.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large oven pan.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Cooking time may be decreased by increasing oven temperature to 300°.

title: crab chowder
directions: Saute onion, broccoli and mushrooms in margarine.
Combine all ingredients in pot and heat almost to a boil.
Serve hot with French bread.

title: old-fashioned bread stuffing for 12 pound turkey
directions: Cook onion and celery in butter until tender.
Mix seasonings and sprinkle over bread cubes.
Add onion mixture and water and combine.
Stuff turkey and roast immediately.

title: debbie's cream of broccoli soup
directions: Clean broccoli, remove stems and cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Steam in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Do not drain.
Melt butter in saucepan, add flour to make paste.
Add chicken stock, stirring with wire whip.
Bring to boil, reduce heat to low.
Stir in broccoli, cream or milk, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil.

title: frozen bananas
directions: Melt chocolate chips in microwave, then dip bananas in chocolate and roll in nuts.
Freeze for about 2 hours.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix all the ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not brown too much. Cool.

title: broccoli and pea salad
directions: Thaw broccoli; drain well and squeeze out all water.
Thaw peas on paper towels.
Put vegetables in bowl. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together and toss with vegetables.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato paste, salt and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Combine other ingredients except cheeses, using 1/2 cup of cooled sauce. Shape and put in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Pour remaining sauce over meat loaf; sprinkle with cheeses and bake 10 minutes more.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix all together in a bowl.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Blend cake mix, eggs, oil and sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle 1/2 of sugar/cinnamon mixture over cake mix and swirl. Pour other 1/2 cake mix in pan and sprinkle with last of sugar/cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until firm.
Mix 4x sugar, milk and vanilla; pour over warm cake.
Cool.

title: broccoli a la mary
directions: Make sauce of first 4 ingredients.
Add cheeses.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: butter mochi
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except for the sesame seed or coconut.
Batter should not be lumpy.
Pour into 2 (8 or 9-inch) square or round cake pans.
Sprinkle the sesame seed or the coconut flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.
Toothpick should come out clean when inserted in the middle.

title: percolator punch
directions: Pour juices in percolator.
Place sugar and spices in basket of perc. Brew and serve piping hot.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake covered in a greased casserole dish for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown meat, adding onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Stir in seasoning, Ragu sauce and water.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.

title: cheesy bacon roll-ups
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Divide into 4 rectangles.
Spread each rectangle with cream cheese.
Sprinkle with bacon bits.
Roll up from short side.
Cut each into 3 pieces.
Bake at 375° until done, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions until well cooked. Spread on bottom of 9 X 13 pan. Layer the greenbeans over the meat mixture. Spoon the soup evenly over the beans. Cover with mashed potatoes like frosting. Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak dried apricots in warm water for 30 minutes.
Drain and cut up.
Mix sugar, butter, egg, water and orange juice thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together. Combine these two mixtures and blend in apricots and nuts.
Grease loaf pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: spanish hamburger
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cook down, stirring occasionally.
Serve on buns.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Place butter on top and cover.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake at 350° in an oblong 9 x 13-inch pan for about 30 to 40 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
While cake is baking, prepare topping.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix all ingredients. Boil 10 minutes. Add food coloring. Boil 5 minutes. Strain and pour into jars. Seal.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and ingredients until done.
Add milk and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: geneva's cereal treats
directions: In a saucepan, mix Karo, brown sugar, oleo and vanilla together.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Then pour syrup mixture over Cheerios and nuts.
Coat well; put in a large deep pan.
Toast 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Stir a few times to keep from sticking. Pour out on wax paper to cool.
Store in covered container.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Blend all together and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Mix in egg and molasses, blending well.
Mix flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to the creamed mixture, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: angel food surprise
directions: Bake cake as directed; cool.
Cut cake in half.
Cut out 1- inch trench on bottom.
Spoon in 1 cup of sliced strawberries. Put top of cake on.
Mix yogurt, Cool Whip and 1/2 cup of crushed strawberries.
Cover cake with this mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: orange blossom cooler
directions: Combine concentrate and water.
Put sherbet and ice cream in bottom of punch bowl.
Pour juice over mixture, stir until partially melted.
Makes 40 - 1/2 oz. cups.
5 quarts.

title: captain mcgowan's roast
directions: Season roast.
Before 11:00 a.m. preheat oven to 375°.
Cook roast in open pan for one hour.
Turn off oven.
Do not open door. Leave roast in oven.
At 6:00 p.m. turn oven on to 375°.
When oven reaches that temperature, start timing; 15 minutes for rare, 20 minutes for medium and 25 minutes for well done.
Take roast out of oven immediately and serve.
Works well for almost any size roast.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Roll into marble-size balls. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 20.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Make into balls and shape as desired.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot.
These freeze well.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook 6 servings of grits as shown on package.
Add butter, cheese, and 2 eggs plus enough milk to make 1 cup.
Cook at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: baked fish
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix juice, onion and butter.
Dip fish in butter mixture.
Place in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour remaining butter mixture over fish.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes or until fish flakes easy with fork.

title: baked cinnamon apples
directions: Core the baking apples almost to the bottom.
Peel skin 1 inch down around the apples.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, flour and cinnamon; fill apples with sugar mixture and place in baking dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 5 minutes or until apples are tender.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms and scallops.
Add soups, celery and cheeses. Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes (covered the first 30 minutes).

title: strawberry punch
directions: Boil sugar and water 3 minutes and let cool.
Combine all the ingredients and add the amount of water called for on lemonade can.
Let freeze solid.
Thaw 2 hours before serving (keep breaking apart with fork).

title: cabbage freebe
directions: Brown ground beef in large, 6-quart pan.
Add seasonings and stir well.
Add cabbage; stir.
When the cabbage is fully cooked, add soup, 1/2 can of milk and 1/2 can of water.
Serve when completely heated.
This is a diabetic dish.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Mix all other ingredients together. Pour into pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix
wet and dry ingredients separately, then together. Roll in a ball and press semi-flat on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs in mixer bowl for 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift in next 6 ingredients, mix well.
Spread in a greased 10 x 15 inch baking pan lined with wax paper.
Sprinkle with nuts (optional).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: mozzarella puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C). Make an indentation in the top of each uncooked biscuit. Fill indentations with oregano and a Mozzarella cube. Pinch the dough around the Mozzarella cubes. Place the biscuits, pinched side down, on a medium ungreased baking sheet.
Cover with pizza sauce. Bake in the preheated oven 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix beaten eggs and sugar well.
Add pumpkin and oil.
Mix well.
Mix dry ingredients together and add alternately to mixture with water.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans and pour in.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour 1/2 batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, unwrap caramels and melt with evaporated milk and margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Pour mixture over hot cake, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans on top of caramel mixture.
Top with remaining cake batter.
Bake 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Steam until tender; drain.
Mash until smooth.
Add egg, flour, salt and baking powder, mixing well.
Form into patties and fry in deep hot oil.

title: *ma elsie gue's homemade mincemeat
directions: Cook beef slowly in hot water to cover until quite tender, about 3 hours.
Chop beef.
Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Let stand, covered at room temperature, for about 5 days.
Freeze in 1 pint packages.
Use 1 pint for making 1 (8-inch) pie.
When making pie, may add 2 to 3 tablespoons of canned bought mincemeat to add to taste.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well. Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Uncover the last 1/2 hour of baking.

title: company casserole
