directions: In bowl, combine beans, corn, soup, sour cream and cheese. Pour in an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine butter, cracker crumbs and almonds; sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water and salt until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Butter large baking dish.
Pour mixture into dish. Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 15 people.
To reheat, put into oven at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Blend in sugar, egg, flour, butter, baking soda and walnuts.
Pour into a lightly greased bread pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Remove 1 cup cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix with 1/2 cup margarine and 1 egg.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: Sprinkle the roast with 1 tablespoon flour.
In a roasting pan, brown the roast on all sides in half of the butter.
Dissolve the bouillon cubes in the water.
Add this mixture, onion, celery, salt and pepper to the meat.
Bring to a boil.
Take off the heat, cover and put into a 350° preheated oven.
Cook for 1 hour.
Add the carrots and potatoes; cover and cook 45 to 60 minutes longer or until meat is tender.
Remove meat and vegetables to serving platter and keep warm.
Strain cooking juices; set aside.

title: butterscotch dips
directions: Melt in double boiler.
Keep in hot water and dip.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix the soups, water and rice together.
Dip chicken in 1/2 stick melted butter.
Pour	mixture
in casserole dish and lay chicken on top.
Cover and	bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 4 or 6.

title: old fashioned pea soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cover peas with 2 quarts water; soak overnight.
Add ham bone, onion, garlic salt, marjoram and pepper. Bring to boiling.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bone; cut off meat.
Dice meat and return to soup with celery and carrot.
Cook slowly for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add salt to taste.
Serve.

title: chicken brunswick stew(low-fat)
directions: In the chicken broth, cook the onions, potato and celery until tender.
Add the chicken, carrots, creamed corn and tomatoes. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cracked pepper, liquid smoke, Worcestershire sauce, salt and Tabasco.
Serves 10.
Has 149 calories and 2 g fat.

title: candied yams
directions: Cook potatoes.
Peel, halve lengthwise and arrange in greased shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and heat to boiling, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over sweet potatoes.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes, basting with syrup once or twice.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 30 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix cheese with mayonnaise; add onions, celery, water chestnuts and drained mixed vegetables.
Mix well.
Put mixture in a buttered casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers fine and mix with melted margarine.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate chip pie mix
directions: Combine sugar and flour; place in airtight plastic bag.
Tie with ribbon and label "dry ingredients."
Place coconut, chocolate morsels and pecans in a second airtight plastic bag; tie with ribbon and label "chocolate packet." Place both in decorated box or bag tied with ribbon.
Yield:
One gift.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.

title: lemony hollandaise sauce
directions: Use a small, heavy pot.
Squeezing a whole lemon into it, add egg yolks.
Add butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly. When butter is melted, cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Remove and serve.

title: cassava cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except for eggs and condensed milk. Spread mix on 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.
Mix eggs and condensed milk and spread over top and bake until brown.

title: sausage enchiladas
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet.
Pour over cream cheese in bowl.
Mix until cream cheese is blended.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and mix well.
Spread tortillas with thin layer of refried beans, then place 1/4 cup meat mixture in center with a pinch of cheese and roll up.
Place in greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hyden salad or ripe tomato relish
directions: Mix tomatoes, cabbage, onions, hot peppers, sweet peppers, salt and celery together; let stand for 2 hours.
Drain and squeeze out water.
Bring vinegar to a boil and add all other ingredients.
Add to tomato mixture and boil for 30 minutes.
Can in pint jars and seal.

title: crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and beat well.
Add oil, flour, salt, vanilla and soda.
Mix well.
Add oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Sift again with dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast, dissolved in warm water.
Mix well.
Pat or roll out on floured wax paper.
Cut and cook on greased pan in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
This does not need to rise and will keep well in refrigerator several days.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the lettuce in a large bowl and add the remaining ingredients in layers.
Chill before serving.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Drain, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve hot or cold.

title: rosemary's mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Pour pudding in pan.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Drain tuna and rinse.
Break it up fine with a fork.
Add soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Add peas and noodles.
Mix. Butter a casserole.
Pour in 1/3 of mixture.
Top with potato chips.
Add in layers with chips on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: garden pizza
directions: *Use any of these you like or all.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Put in hot sterile jars and seal.

title: peg leg salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, water and celery seed.
Boil 3 minutes and pour over rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lime jello
directions: Mix hot water, jello, pineapple juice, sliced bananas and pineapple.
Top with little marshmallows.
Refrigerate.

title: soy marinade for broiled salmon steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour over steaks and marinate for 20 to 30 minutes, turning several times.
Broil or grill on barbecue to desired doneness.
Do not overcook!
We do about 5 minutes one side, 7 minutes the other side (depends on thickness of steaks).
Also good on shrimp.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onions, raisins and water chestnuts.
Blend sugar, vinegar, cream, salad dressing, salt, pepper and paprika. Pour dressing over veggies.
Add bacon and nuts before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: dirt cake recipe
directions: Mix everything except cookies, Cool Whip and gummy worms. Fold in Cool Whip.
Grind up cookies.
Put a layer of cookies in a floured dish, then a layer of pudding mix.
Put one more layer of each and then end with a layer of cookies.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Place flowers and gummy worms on top.
Very good. Looks great in flowerpot.

title: cavatini
directions: Mix hamburger with onions, sauces, green pepper and brown sugar.
Simmer while cooking pasta.
Add cooked pasta and place in a 9 x 13 pan with sauce. Sprinkle Mozzarella on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cheese is melted. If everything is hot only bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Slice chicken breast into thin strips.
Toss with apple, celery and mayonnaise.
Garnish with sliced ripe mango or pineapple if desired.
Makes 1 serving.

title: ocean in a bottle
directions: Rinse bottle.
Remove all labels.
Fill one-half full with water and then one-quarter full of oil.
Add a few drops of food coloring.
Tightly replace cap.

title: honey-whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir in honey, salt, shortening, water and whole wheat flour. Beat until smooth.
Stir in flour.
Knead 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Punch down.
Divide in half. Shape into 2 loaves. Place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on wire rack.

title: easy beef stew with rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add meat and onions; cook and stir until meat is browned.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in tomatoes, mushrooms, broth, carrots and garlic powder.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain the vermicelli or thin spaghetti.
Add chopped vegetables.
Pour salad dressing over mixture to taste (about 1 cup).
Shake on Supreme seasoning generously.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 1 hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine first five salad ingredients together sprinkling bacon on top. Set aside.
Combine remaining dressing ingredients. Cook until mixture thickens. Cool. Toss with salad greens or pour over individual bowls of salad mix.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, except pecans; mix well. Chill.
Shape into a ball; roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple millionaire pie
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add egg, salt and vanilla.
Mix until light and fluffy.
Spoon evenly into pie crust.
Chill. Whip cream until stiff and blend in pineapple and nuts. Spoon on top of egg mixture and chill thoroughly.
Makes two pies.

title: old-fashioned chocolate gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a 10 x 12 baking pan and dust it with fine bread crumbs.
Shake out excess crumbs.
Sift the flour, baking soda, salt, ginger, cinnamon and allspice together.
Melt chocolate.
Let cool until warm.
Mix butter and hot coffee until butter is completely melted.
Mix in brown sugar.
Mix in molasses. Beat in the eggs.
Pour in the chocolate and mix well.
Beat in the dry ingredients lightly.
Stir in the candied ginger.
The mixture should be fairly thin.
Pour the mixture into the pan, making sure it is level.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Let cool for 20 minutes. Invert onto a cookie sheet.
Then invert onto serving plate and let cool before serving.
Makes two dozen squares.

title: eggplant rollatini with three cheeses
directions: Sprinkle the eggplant slices lightly with salt on both sides and let them drain in a colander for 30 minutes. In a food processor chop fine the feta, add the ricotta, egg, 1/2 cup parmesan and lemon juice blend until smooth. Add 1/4 cup parsley and scallions and process the mixture for 10 seconds. Transfer the eggplant slices to paper towels and pat them dry. Arrange 1/3 of the eggplant slices in one layer on a jelly roll pan brushed with oil and brush the tops with oil. Cook the eggplant slices under a preheated broiler about 4 inches from the heat turning them once and brushing them again with the oil for 8-10 minutes or until lightly browned on both sides. Transfer them to paper towels to drain and cook the remaining slices in the same manner. Put 2 Tbsp. of the cheese mixture at the short end of each slice and roll up slices to enclose filling. Spread 1/4 cup of the sauce in a 10 x 7 baking pan and arrange the eggplant rolls in one layer on the sauce. Pour the remaining sauce over the rolls and sprinkle it with the remaining 1/4 cup of parmesan.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Store in jars.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup boiling water.

title: shredded wheat raised rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients except yeast and flour.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Add yeast and flour; let rise until double.
Punch down and let rise again (not necessary).
Put dough on lightly floured board and knead slightly.
Cut into rolls and put in well-greased pan to rise.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes. May need to cover with foil after 10 minutes to keep from browning.

title: butternut bisque
directions: My market peels and seeds their squash, which is very handy as it must be done for this soup.
Cut it and set aside.
Melt the butter in a large soup pot; add the carrots, onion and celery; saute until soft.
Stir the squash and potatoes into the vegetables.
Add the stock; bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, partially covered, for 40 minutes.
Add curry, nutmeg and ginger. Puree the soup in batches in a blender.
Return to saucepan; add more stock if necessary to thin; salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot with a dollop of sour cream if you like.
Serves 6.

title: chicken divan
directions: Parboil chicken breasts, cut in strips. Cook broccoli until it separates.
Mix soup and lemon juice with mayonnaise.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish with uncooked rice.
On top, add sliced onions, green pepper, 1 can stewed tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Add water to cover rice.
Brown pork chops on one side.
Put brown side down on rice.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Take off foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: cherry pineapple crumble
directions: Mix pineapple and cherry pie filling in bottom of cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 box of cake mix over top. Drizzle melted butter over this and bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until the cake mix turns golden brown.
Goes great with vanilla ice cream on the side.
Serves 6.

title: bo bo chicken
directions: Place everything in 9 x 13 pan. Cover and put in the refrigerator for 1 hour. Turn chicken and leave sit for 1 more hour. Pour entire contents into saucepan and cook until approximately 1 cup of sauce remains. Serve over rice or noodles. Excellent flavor.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar well, then add milk, vanilla, salt and cream.
Beat until sugar is dissolved.
Freeze in an ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's directions.

title: chicken wing drumsticks
directions: Remove and discard wing tips.
Separate remaining wing sections.
Cut skin at small end of each wing section.
Pull out one of the bones from section, having 2 bones; set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small skillet, toast sesame seed over low heat until golden, stirring occasionally.
In a small shallow bowl, combine toasted seed, breadcrumbs, paprika, salt and seasoned salt.
Dip wing sections into half and half, then into breadcrumb mixture.
Arrange in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes in preheated oven until tender.
Makes 24 appetizer servings.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Reserve one cup chicken broth.
Combine soups, green chilies, spices, Tabasco sauce and chicken broth. Blend well.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute celery and onion in bacon drippings.
Add soup and milk.
Combine with broccoli, salt, pepper and rice.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Cover with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: apple squares
directions: Beat eggs 1 minute; add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla, oil and dry ingredients.
Stir until all is moistened.
Add nuts, apples and raisins.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese almond ball
directions: Beat cheese, milk, onion and 3/4 cup almonds until well blended.
Chill at least one hour.
Form into a ball and wrap in waxed paper and chill several hours or overnight.
Chop remaining almonds; add parsley.
Roll ball in this mixture and serve with assorted crackers.

title: strawberry parfait ring
directions: Cook sugar with water until syrup spins on thread (235°).
Add a few drops of red food coloring.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gradually add hot syrup.
Continue beating until cool and light; add vanilla and salt.
Fold in the whipped cream and pour into a 2-quart ring mold and freeze.
At serving time, unmold and fill center with berries and sprinkle a fluff of coconut on top.
If ring is not tinted, use coconut tinted pink.
Border the ring with whipped cream puffs.
Whip 1 cup heavy cream until fairly stiff. Drop from spoon onto baking sheet or flat pan to make little mound and freeze.
Put whole strawberry on each puff just before serving.

title: cheesy potato surprise
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks and boil until tender.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Take 1 teaspoon oil and oil 9 x 12 x 1-inch pan. Sprinkle pan with bread crumbs.
Drain potatoes and in large bowl add olive oil and mash potatoes.
Add milk, egg, tomato paste and garlic.
Stir in cheese.
Place in 9 x 12 x 1-inch (or so) pan, making it as level as possible.
Sprinkle extra bread crumbs across top to make crust.
Bake 40 minutes.
Cool 15.
This is an excellent variation of mashed potatoes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir until well blended.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: wilson cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Bake at 375° in 8-inch round pan for 25 minutes.

title: lemon bread(2nd place at montgomery co. fair, maryland)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating until smooth.
Into another bowl, sift flour, powder and salt.
Stir mixture alternately with milk into the sugar mixture.
Stir in nuts (if desired) and zest.
Put in well buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or 3 mini loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour for large loaf pan, 30 to 40 minutes for mini pans or until pick comes out clean.
Transfer to rack; heat 1/4 cup sugar and lemon juice until sugar is dissolved.
Poke holes all over the lemon bread and pour glaze over top.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Peel
cooled
potatoes and mash well.
Mix spices, salt and sugar into mashed potatoes.
Mix well, then add one egg at a time,
stirring
well after each.
Slowly add cream and mix well. Pour
into unbaked pastry shell. Bake in preheated oven at	350° until
done,
approximately
minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil in a very large saucepan. Add soda, bring to boil again and add pecans.
Stir constantly, continuing to firm ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat until it thickens and loses its shiny gloss.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Add teaspoon hot water if it becomes too hard.
May be frozen or kept in airtight container.
A teaspoon of vanilla may be added at end of cooking, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Combine with all other ingredients and pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Pour 1/2 stick melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pepperoni salad
directions: Cut up lettuce, cauliflower and cut carrots in bite-size pieces.
Add pepperoni and cheese.
Mix all together.
Add the dressing 15 minutes before serving and mix well.

title: venison goulash
directions: Saute hamburger meat, onion and pepper.
Season to taste. Prepare noodles as directed on package.
Mix drained meat and noodles together.
Add tomato juice and heat thoroughly.
Water or milk may be added depending on desired thickness.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let this mixture sit out all day in a plastic bowl (not metal) covered with wax paper.
At the end of the day, pour mixture into a jar and cover with lid loosely.
Refrigerate 3 to 5 days (not less than 3, not more than 5).

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in a large mixing bowl; beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to zucchini mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Turn into 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in 350° gas oven for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pans 5 minutes.
Remove and finish cooling on rack. Makes 2 loaves.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese cold then let come to room temperature for better mixing and shaping of balls.
Mix cheese, Bisquick and sausage; form 1 1/2-inch balls which may be flattened with a fork. Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until brown at 350°.
This does well baked and then frozen.
Heat just before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Place bread and sausage in 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Blend other ingredients and pour over sausage and bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: biscuit doughnuts
directions: Open biscuit can and separate biscuits.
Take one and form into a doughnut gently, then in sugar and sprinkle cinnamon on top, then place on cookie sheet.
Continue to do this to other biscuits and when all placed on cookie sheet, put in oven to bake for 5 to 8 minutes until golden brown; cool and eat.

title: granny's bran muffins
directions: Soak All-Bran in milk for 5 minutes.
Add beaten egg and brown and white sugars.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to bran mixture.
Add oil and raisins or nuts.
Mix together and place in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add liquid to dry mixture.
Stir just until moist, should be slightly lumpy.
Pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: orange pecans
directions: Proceed as for Spiced Pecans.

title: swedish apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and blend well.
Sift soda, nutmeg, flour, cinnamon and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Bake in well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove and spread with topping.

title: easy cherry cheese cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch dish, cover bottom with slices of pound cake. Mix next 4 ingredients until spreadable.
Spread over cake. Cover with cherry pie filling.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: tv nibbles(50 servings)
directions: Melt oleo; add seasonings.
Pour over all ingredients; mix well.
Place in large flat pan in a 200° oven for 2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, and salt.
Add butter, milk, chopped nuts, and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Mix together and sprinkle over batter:
1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour 1 cup hot water over cake.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with ice cream. May be doubled for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ambrosia fruit dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and yogurt until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit, cheese cubes or melon balls.
May also be used as topping for fruit salad.

title: layer salad
directions: Chop the first 5 items.
Place in layers in 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Sprinkle peas over first five items.
Spread mayonnaise and sprinkle sugar over mayonnaise.
Slice eggs over mayonnaise. Cover with grated cheese.
Add bacon bits.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain; rinse with cold water.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except cherry tomatoes and Parmesan cheese.
Cover; refrigerate 4 to 6 hours to blend flavors.
Just before serving, add tomatoes; mix lightly.
Garnish with olives; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Combine eggs, oil and strawberries.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing well with mixer. Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until a pick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Can be baked in 3 aluminum-foil pans, using Pam instead of greasing pans. Enjoy!

title: sugarless banana and walnut cake
directions: In bowl, beat bananas and margarine until creamy.
Add eggs. Beat well.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to banana mixture alternately with water.
Add nuts.
Spoon into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown
meat in salted skillet.
Drain meat.
Mix tomato sauce, tomato paste, onion, garlic, Italian seasoning, pepper, oregano, sugar,
salt
and
mushrooms in saucepan.
Add meat, cook
over medium heat stirring frequently until sauce reaches slow
boil. Reduce
heat
to
lowest
heat
and
simmer, stir occasionally. Preheat
oven to 350°.
Prepare lasagna noodles according to directions on package.
Cover bottom of dish with a layer of noodles;
use
1/2 of sauce to cover noodles, then add 1/2 Ricotta
followed
by
Mozzarella, use remaining noodles to cover cheeses.
Add the rest of the sauce, Ricotta and Mozzarella. Bake
for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbling.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and drain.
Add salt and pepper. Grease a 10-inch pie pan.
Add meat mixture and press down.
Add cheese.
Mix eggs, Bisquick mix and milk.
Blend well.
Pour over layer of cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes before serving.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Peel/cook potatoes for mashed potatoes.
While loaf is cooking, remove crust from slices of bread.
Beat eggs.
Crumble bread into egg mixture.
Add ground beef, mushroom soup, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Mix very well.
Grease loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Check loaf for doneness.
Grate cheese onto top of loaf.
Put mashed potatoes on top of cheese.
Put back in oven to melt cheese.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large frying pan; saute eggplant for 5 minutes or slightly soft.
Combine 1/2 cup hot water, beef stock base and spaghetti sauce seasoning; pour over eggplant.
Cover; simmer until tender and liquid is absorbed.
Spoon into flat baking dish.
Combine sour cream, onion flakes, salt and pepper. Pour over casserole.
Cover with crumbs, sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; separate eggs.
Add yolks, oleo and salt, cooking in a double boiler until thick.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Mix egg whites, cream of tartar and water.
Beat until whites peak; slowly add sugar.
Cover filling in shell with the meringue mixture and bake at 300° until lightly browned.

title: prince of wales cake(dates from 1860's)
directions: Beat 6 eggs very lightly and add them to 1/2 pound of butter. Work until light.
Beat all together until light and gradually put in 1 pound of flour containing 2 teaspoons of baking powder and 1 cup water.
Stir into the batter one teaspoon each of the ground cinnamon, allspice, cloves and nutmeg.
Cut into small pieces the 1/2 pound of citron and 1 pound of seedless raisins.
Wash and dry one pound currants.
Stir into the batter and bake in a quicker oven than necessary for other cakes, covering the top to prevent burning.
Bake until done.

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Combine apples, water and honey or molasses in small saucepan. Cover.
Cook on stovetop or in microwave until water boils.
Stir in remaining ingredients until cooks, 1 minute, stirring so it won't burn and apples are soft.
Let cool slightly.
Serve warm over frozen yogurt or ice cream.

title: fried peanut butter and jelly sandwiches
directions: Take 2 slices of bread and spread butter on both slices, then spread peanut butter on one slice of bread and jelly on the other slice.
Put the sandwich in a skillet with 1 teaspoon of butter and cook until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, nutmeg and cinnamon to preceding mixture and mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Grease pans.
Makes 5 loaves (3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch). Use any size pan.
Fill pans 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for about an hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: busy woman's casserole
directions: Place rice in a greased casserole dish.
Stir consomme into rice.
Place pork chops on top; pour onion soup over all.
Cover and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.
Yields 4 servings. Good served with a green salad and a light dessert.

title: broccoli and cheese muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spoon into muffin tin which has been sprayed with Baker's Joy.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: spiced carrots
directions: Cut carrots into 3-inch long very thin sticks.
Blanch in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain and cool under cold water. Drain again and place in bowl.

title: hot cocktail sausages
directions: Heat all ingredients except sausages.
When hot, add sausages and simmer until ready to use.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Boil and dice potatoes.
Season lightly with salt, pepper and margarine.
Combine sour cream, soup, onion and cheese.
Pour over potatoes with dry cereal.
Drizzle with melted margarine. Place in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: fettucini with creamy chicken
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips.
Peel and chop onion.
In skillet, saute chicken strips in half the butter until lightly brown on all sides.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in jam.
Sift together dry ingredients, adding little at a time with milk.
Stir in raisins.
Pour batter into 2 greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well and pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into 3-inch squares and serve on a lettuce leaf.
Yield: 9 servings.

title: mint brownies
directions: Prepare fudge brownie mix according to directions; cool completely.
Mix softened butter, powdered sugar, peppermint extract and green food coloring with enough milk to make mixture spreadable.
Spread on top of cooled brownies.
Put into freezer for 1 hour.
Melt butter and chocolate chips in saucepan; spread over frozen brownies.
Refrigerate; cut when cold.

title: basic pot roast
directions: Put vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Salt and pepper the meat.
Put it in the pot.
Add the liquid and cover the pot.
Cook it on low, 10 to 12 hours.

title: california citrus cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add cake mix, pudding mix, water and oil.
Beat 10 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
Melt chocolate and butter in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
When completely melted, remove from heat and set aside.
Beat 3 eggs until well blended.
Slowly beat in 2 cups of sugar and beat for 1 minute.
Add flour, salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla, mixing well.
Add the melted chocolate and mix well. Spread half of chocolate batter into prepared pan.

title: frozen lemon sandwiches
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan or dish with whole graham crackers (broken at perforated lines).
Mix together the can of sweetened milk, lemonade and Cool Whip.
Pour over graham crackers.
Then put crackers on top.
Place in freezer until firm. Slice and serve.

title: strawberry soda cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box.
When cake is done, let cool. Punch holes in cake with fork.
Mix jello and soda together and pour over cake.
Mix pudding as directed on box and pour over cake.
Then spread Cool Whip over the pudding.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: taco pie dip
directions: Spread ingredients in order as above on 10 inch pie plate or dish at least that size.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, dressing, eggs, water and cinnamon, mixing at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool. Spread with frosting.
Preparation time:
25 minutes.
Baking time:
35 minutes plus cooling.
Makes 12 servings.

title: greek macaroni
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water and 2 teaspoons salt to a boil over high heat.
Add macaroni all at once.
Stir constantly. Cook as package directs until pasta is tender.
Drain.
Heat 2 tablespoons oleo in a 10-inch skillet. Add chopped onion and saute slowly until it turns golden.
Add meat.
Break up. Saute until it loses its red color.
Add tomato sauce, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Simmer 20 minutes. Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add half the macaroni. Top with meat sauce, spreading evenly over macaroni.
Add remaining macaroni. Preheat oven to 350°.
In
a medium saucepan, melt remaining 3 tablespoons oleo. Stir in flour. Remove from heat. Slowly stir in milk.
Beat until smooth. Simmer 5 minutes until thick.
Cool slightly.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs slightly with a wire whisk. Slowly add half of the hot cream sauce, beating constantly. Return mixture to remaining sauce in pan and beat until smooth. Season to taste.
Pour sauce over all. Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork tenderloin medallions
directions: Mix flour and lemon pepper.
Roll pork in this and brown in butter.
Remove to a platter.
Combine remaining ingredients in skillet.
Bring to a boil to melt sugar and break up tomatoes. Return pork to skillet, lower heat and cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove pork to platter.
Cool 15 minutes.
Slice 3/8-inch thick pieces.
Continue cooking sauce until thickened.
Serve with yellow rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into a ball, then roll in walnuts and top with a cherry.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: Melt chocolate in water.
Add Eagle Brand milk and cook until thick, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Pour into plain or graham cracker crust. Top with Cool Whip (optional).

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Cook broccoli and put into 2-quart glass bake dish.
Heat until melted cream cheese, mushroom soup and milk; pour over broccoli.
Do not stir.
Cover top with buttered Ritz crackers. Bake until brown and hot at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: florida chops
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan and drain off oil.
Mix orange juice, honey, salt, cornstarch and orange peel.
Baste chops and place in slow cooker.
Pour extra juice on chops.
Cook 6 to 8 hours in crock-pot.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Mix with apples.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Beat sour cream, egg and vanilla.
Pour over apple mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes and then at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with crumb topping. Bake 10 minutes more at 400°.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain salmon and flake.
Add cream cheese, lemon juice, onion and horseradish.
Mix well.
Chill well!
Shape into a log and roll in nuts.
Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers or party rye.

title: gazpacho soup*
directions: Combine all things, except onion, pepper and cucumber.
Blend well.
Add onion, pepper and cucumber.
Experiment!
I use what I have and substitute V-8 instead of tomato juice.
The longer it sits, the better it is!

title: green beans with tomato relish
directions: Saute tomato, celery, pepper and onion in oil until tender-crisp.
Stir in ketchup, vinegar, sugar, basil, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes. Cover and chill thoroughly.
Spoon tomato relish over beans and garnish with fresh basil.

title: beef wellingtons
directions: Combine biscuit mix and 2/3 cup milk in bowl, mixing well. Knead lightly on floured surface.
Roll into 8 x 12-inch rectangle. Cut into 8 equal rectangles.
Combine next 8 ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon dry mustard in bowl, mixing well.
Shape into eight 4-inch long rolls.
Place 1 roll on each dough rectangle, rolling to enclose filling.
Seal seams, leaving ends open.
Place side seam down in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Mix soup, 1/2 cup milk and remaining 1/2 teaspoon dry mustard in saucepan.
Cook until heated through, stirring frequently.
Pour over ground beef rolls.
Serves 8.

title: goop
directions: Mix cornstarch with water and optional coloring.
Pour mixture onto a tray or make in a large tub.
Experience and enjoy this unique mixture's properties.
Keep reusing Goop.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Combine
sugar,
water	and
cream
of tartar. Bring to boil; boil
minute.
Add crackers and boil 2 more minutes. Pour
into unbaked pie shell. Add cinnamon and butter.
Place top crust on pie.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine.
Mix together and roll into a ball.
Chill well.

title: shrimp cocktail(4 servings)
directions: Wash, shell, devein and boil shrimp.
Mix all other ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with prepared shrimp.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix in order given. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in 9 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbled graham crackers on top of butter. Sprinkle chocolate chips and butterscotch chips on top of cracker crumbs.
Dribble sweetened condensed milk on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix shortening, sugar and salt; add to yeast.
Mix the 2 flours and add to other mix.
Blend. Put in greased bowl and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and make into rolls and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: red beans and rice
directions: In a large pot filled 3/4 full of water, add beans and cook until water is below bean level.
In a large skillet, saute onion, garlic, sausage and ham until the onion is translucent.
Put ingredients in pot with beans. Refill pot with hot water and cook until the water has turned into a thick gravy.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook rice separately.
Serve red beans over the rice.

title: eggs benedict
directions: Butter a split, toasted English muffin.
Cover with ham slice; top each with poached egg.
Cover with Hollandaise Sauce.

title: peanut butter dip
directions: Combine ingredients and beat on low speed until well blended. Serve with apple slices or banana chunks. Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Beat rest of ingredients until smooth.
Spread rest of ingredients on top of refried beans.
Top with shredded lettuce, 1 to 2 diced tomatoes and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with Tostitos or corn chips.

title: grape-nuts custard
directions: Scald the milk.
Add margarine.
To beaten eggs, add sugar, salt, vanilla and Grape-Nuts; combine with milk.
Pour into large oval-size aluminum pan.
Bake in pan of water at 375° for 1 hour. Makes 35 to 40 servings.

title: carrot-pineapple bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Makes 2 regular size loaves or 3 in foil loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: fruit tarts
directions: Fold fruit into pastry and pinch shut like a small apple pie. Spread on butter and lay tart on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 10 minutes or until a soft brown and very flaky.
Delicious and easy!

title: ranch chicken breast
directions: Whisk juice and dressing mix together.
Marinate chicken in 1/2 juice mix for 2 to 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Combine cornstarch, water and remaining juice mixture in saucepan. Heat until thickened.
Brush chicken with sauce.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (very small amount of salt, if desired); put in oblong 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick butter and mix with 1 stack crushed Ritz crackers.
Top vegetable mixture with the buttered crackers and bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes.
This is good made the night before and refrigerated.
Fix the cracker mix just before baking.
It also freezes well without the cracker topping.
Serves about 8.

title: he-man scalloped potatoes
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and butter.
Add soup and milk.
Stir. In 2-quart casserole, arrange potatoes and soup.
Mix alternately. Add 4 thin slices of American cheese and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more or until tender.

title: baked chicken or turkey
directions: Mix dry ingredients and rub into chicken or turkey. Refrigerate overnight in a Baggie.
The next day, fill the whole chicken or turkey breast with the chopped onion.
Place in a foil-lined pan and bake for 5 hours at 250°.
Very spicy.
Good hot or cold.

title: cherry drop cake
directions: Bake a white Duncan Hines cake, then spread cream cheese on the cake.
Spread whipped cream on the cake, then drop pie filling cherries on the cake.
Don't spread the cherries, just take a spoon and drop them.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Unfold crescent rolls and cut into small pieces of dough (one package should be enough for 1 package of hot dogs).
Roll hot dogs in dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully.
Remove when dough is golden brown.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered dish. Bake at 350°.

title: beans and ham aloha
directions: In a large bowl, combine beans and ham.
Pour into 2 quart casserole.
Top with pineapple slices and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg until moist.
Pat dough into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first six ingredients and cook.
When thick enough to set it off, add margarine and vanilla.
Stir and put into pie shell.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Fry onions and peppers in butter.
Add meat and blend thoroughly, add seasonings.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs and mix well.
Put 1 cup of corn in baking dish, then half of the meat mixture, a layer of tomatoes and repeat layers.
Cover with crumbs, dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
During last 30 minutes of baking time top with corn flakes mixed with 1 stick of butter.

title: large cucumber pickles
directions: Pour water over cukes and lime and soak 24 hours.
Rinse well. Cover with cold water and soak 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: coconut pie crust
directions: Roll into about 11-inch circle.
Cut into 1/2-inch strips. Moisten edge of pie crust with water.
Lay half of strips across filling, spacing them about 3/4 inch apart.
Repeat procedure with remaining strips, arranging in opposite direction.
Press strips to edge of bottom pastry and trim even with overhanging edge of bottom pastry.
Fold the 3/4-inch overhang and strips under, pressing firmly so edge of pastry is even with rim of pie plate.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine topping mix with 1 cup milk and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Beat on high about 6 minutes or until topping thickens and forms peaks.
Add remaining milk and pie filling mix; blend on low.
Beat on high 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally. Spoon into pie shell.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Store in refrigerator.

title: super nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

title: double crust pizza casserole
directions: For
crust
combine flour, potatoes, milk and margarine. Set aside.
In	Dutch
oven
cook beef, sausage and onion until onion is	tender	and
meat
is
brown. Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce,
tomato
paste, seasoning mix and garlic powder. Press 1/2 of the crust in bottom and up the sides of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole
dish.
Spread
filling
over
crust; sprinkle with cheese.
Roll remaining
crust to a 15 x 11-inch rectangle between wax paper and invert over filling.	Trim edges and turn under and crimp.
Bake
at
for
to
35 minutes until golden.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Put sliced cucumbers and onions in large bowl; set aside.
In small mixing bowl, combine salad dressing, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Mix well, then pour over cucumbers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan.
Saute next 4 ingredients until soft.
Slice whole okra; chop whole tomatoes. Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Add okra, tomatoes, liquid chicken bouillon and seasoning to sauteed vegetables.
Bring to a boil, cook and simmer 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and crab and cook 10 minutes.
Ladle into bowls; serve with rice.
Makes 4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: carrot fruit cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, stirring well. Combine eggs, oil, vanilla and pineapple. Add to dry ingredients, stirring until well blended. Add bananas, carrots and pecans, stirring just until blended. Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 20 minutes. Remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.

title: oven glazed chicken
directions: Lightly grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange chicken in dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients. Spoon over chicken. Bake 30 minutes or until done.

title: champignon alfredo
directions: Saute sliced mushrooms in butter, garlic, salt, fine herbs and black pepper.
Add buttermilk and wine.
Cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
May be eaten "as is" or combined with beef, fish, chicken, pasta, vegetables or almost anything. Freezes and microwaves great.
For thicker sauce, substitute sour cream for buttermilk.

title: taco beef soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned; drain off excess fat.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, undrained kidney beans, tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix. Simmer, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with cheese, corn chips and sour cream.

title: sugar cookie jewels
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture.
Mix until blended.

title: stover fudge
directions: Cook as rapidly as possible, stirring constantly, to soft ball stage the first 3 ingredients.
Quickly add marshmallows, chips and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool and slice.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Cook and stir the first 4 ingredients until thick.
Pour small amount into yolks.
Pour yolks into pan; cook about 5 minutes. Add lemon juice, rind and butter; pour into shell.
Top with meringue.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 300° oven until brown.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and serve with Ritz crackers or any good crackers.

title: heath bar dessert
directions: Crush crackers; melt oleo.
Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the pudding, milk and ice cream; spread over crumbs.
Cover with Dream Whip or Cool Whip.
Crush the Heath bars and spread on top.
Cool 4 hours in refrigerator.

title: grapenut pudding
directions: Bring milk to a boil; add Grape-Nuts.
Let stand and cool. Beat egg yolks in, adding sugar also.
Mix in pinch of salt and mix well with cooled milk and Grape-Nuts.
Pour in a greased pan and fold in egg whites from 3 eggs.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: stir-fry chicken and broccoli
directions: Stir-fry chicken in hot oil in a large skillet until brown. Add vegetables.
Fry until crispy and tender.
Mix broth, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar, garlic powder and ginger.
Add to chicken and vegetables.
Bring to boil.
Cook for 2 minutes. Prepare rice as directed on package.
Serve chicken and vegetables over rice.

title: rib roast of beef
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together flour, mustard and all other dry seasonings.
Pour Worcestershire sauce over roast and rub all over, then roll roast all around in flour mixture until well coated.
Place in oven pan.
Pour water and wine around roast.
Use meat thermometer to cook to desired doneness.
Keep roast covered until the last 30 minutes of cooking; baste with juices during the last 30 minutes.

title: mexican turkey roll-ups
directions: In a bowl, combine turkey, 1/2 cup sour cream, 1 1/2 tsp. taco seasoning, half of the soup, 1 cup of cheese, onion, salsa and olives.
Place 1/3 cup filling on each tortilla.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine remaining sour cream, taco seasoning and soup; pour over tortillas.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Serve with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes.
Top with additional salsa if desired.
Yields about 5 servings.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Mix egg, pizza sauce, salt, pepper and corn flakes in bowl. Add in ground beef, onion and mushrooms.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press half the mixture in the bottom of an ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place 2 slices cheese side by side on top.
Press remaining meat mixture over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Place remaining cheese on top.
Return to oven until melted.

title: coconut bonbon
directions: Mix and put in refrigerator until firm.
Roll in ball and dip in chocolate, which consists of 1 stick paraffin and 2 packages chocolate chips melted in double boiler.

title: apple sauerkraut salad
directions: Chop sauerkraut real fine with a potato chopper.
Mix all ingredients together. Cover tightly.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Very good.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; cool.
Dice chicken.
Grease casserole bowl with margarine and place about half of the chicken in bowl.
Heat soup and milk; pour half over chicken and top with half of cheese (broken into pieces).
Layer remaining chicken, soup mixture and cheese.
Mix crumbs with margarine; sprinkle over top.
Bake until lightly browned, about 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fruity cottage cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least 2 hours.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix all vegetables and meat and put in large casserole.
Mix juice, Worcestershire sauce, sugar and tapioca and pour over vegetables and meat.
Cover and bake 5 hours at 250°.
Do not brown.
Water may be added if needed to keep moist enough.

title: toasted jarslberg loaf
directions: Remove crust from bread (reserve for bread crumbs).
Slice bread into 1-inch slices without slicing through the bottom of the loaf.
Slice loaf in half lengthwise.
Place on large sheet or foil or baking sheet.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Mix all together.
Grease 2 (8-inch) pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: german soup
directions: Boil until tender.
Feeds a large crowd.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter and cheese with a pastry blender or fork.
Stir in sour cream.
Shape into a ball. Chill 2 hours.

title: country time chicken and noodles
directions: Cook noodles in 2 quarts water.
Shake chicken in flour and seasonings.
Reserve remaining flour.
Fry 5 to 7 minutes, or until
chicken
and
onion	are
browned.
Reduce heat and simmer approximately 45 minutes.
Drain noodles and toss with butter
and parsley.
Keep
warm.
To serve, place noodles on platter	and put chicken on top.
Cover with foil.
Remove all but
2 tablespoons
drippings from skillet.
Stir in reserved flour. Cook about 1 minute, or until golden brown.
Gradually stir
in milk;
bring
to
a
boil.	Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly until
mixture
thickens.
Spoon
some
gravy over noodles and chicken.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and mix well; set aside.
In separate mixing bowl, combine next 4 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to wet ingredients.
Add fruit cocktail; mix well. Pour batter into a greased and floured pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack in jars along with 1/2 teaspoon in bottom of each jar and 1/2 teaspoon on top of cucumbers.
To each jar add 1 small clove garlic and 1 sprig dill.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello; add cream cheese and stir.
Add 7-Up.
When partly set up, fold in pineapple and nuts.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix well.
Chill for an hour or more.
Excellent for fish.

title: cranberry-raspberry punch
directions: Line a large, shallow baking pan with waxed paper.
Using a small ice cream scoop, or 2 (1 tablespoon) measuring spoons, shape frozen yogurt into 20 balls or ovals.
Place on waxed paper. Freeze, covered, for up to 3 days before serving.

title: spiced pumpkin pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
In separate bowl beat milk, pumpkin, eggs and oil.
Add flour mixture and stir to moisten.
On a lightly oiled or nonstick griddle on medium heat, pour batter in 1/4 cup portions, 1-inch apart. Cook until bubbles form on top and bottoms are brown.
Turn.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Lower heat, cook and stir until thick.
Stir a little of the hot mixture into egg. Return to remaining hot mixture.
Bring to a boil, cool then chill.
Fold in whipped cream and vanilla. Pour into pastry shell.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Boil 3 cups of water.
Add the box of pudding and the box of jello.
Bring to a boil, stirring continually.
Let cool!

title: quick cherry slices
directions: Cover a slice of toast with thick applesauce.
Sprinkle with cinnamon
(optional).
Cover
with	a
slice
of American cheese. Broil until cheese melts.

title: banana fritters
directions: Peel bananas and crush.
Add milk, flour and juice.
Mix together and drop by spoonful into hot cooking oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: chicken ratatouille
directions: Chop onion.
Cut pepper into rings.
Slice zucchini.
Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Mince garlic.
Cut chicken into crosswise strips.

title: dumplings
directions: Take flour and butter and mix until it's crumbly.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir until it forms a ball.
Put on a floured board and knead until stiff.
Roll it out and cut in 2 x 4-inch squares. Drop in boiling broth and cook until tender.

title: skewered sesame chicken
directions: Mince enough coriander to measure 1 tablespoons.
Peel ginger and onion; mince/chop ginger and onion.
Place in large bowl with coriander.
Add soy sauce, sherry and oil.

title: cookie pudding
directions: In a small bowl, dip cookies in evaporated milk until soft, not crumbly.
In a 13 x 9-inch dish, place a layer of dipped cookies, then top with Cool Whip.
Repeat with cookies and Cool Whip, ending with Cool Whip.
Chill for 2 hours.
Ready to serve.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Wash and cut up chicken into service size pieces.
Remove all excess fat and skin.
Put flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag. Dip chicken in buttermilk and put in bag with flour.
Shake bag until chicken is coated well.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Shake off excess flour from chicken and put in hot oil to fry.
Cook chicken over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes, turning as needed until light brown.
Reduce heat, cover tightly and cook 30 to 40 minutes or until thickest pieces are fork tender.
Turn chicken once or twice to assure even cooking.
Remove cover for last 5 minutes of cooking to crisp chicken.
Remove from skillet and drain on paper towels before serving hot.

title: rocks
directions: Sift flour with soda, pinch of salt, cloves, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat after each addition.
Add syrup and then stir in flour.
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet and bake in 375° to 400° oven until lightly browned.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Mix flour, powdered milk and salt together.
Work them well. Put yeast and sugar in warm water and let rise.
Mix oil and eggs. Beat together.
After yeast and sugar have risen, add all other ingredients and let rise until double, about 1 hour or more.
Bake at 400° for about 20 or 25 minutes. Brush hot rolls with melted butter.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add water, vanilla and salad dressing.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch prepared pan (spray or oil).
Bake about 20 minutes or until done at 350°. Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: barbecued sandwich(35 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 2 hours in double boiler. Serve on sandwich rolls.

title: date roll
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage.
Add chopped dates and cook again until candy forms a soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat and add chopped nuts.
Stir until candy begins to stiffen slightly.
Pour on smooth cloth which has been dipped in cold water and wrung dry.
Shape candy in small roll and wrap in cloth.
When cool, cut in slices.
Candy may be kept in cloth until ready to eat.

title: basic italian sauce(multi-purpose)
directions: Brown
meat
in
olive oil, stirring as it browns.
Add onions when
almost
done
and
stir and brown a little.
Put spices
in small pan of water and keep simmering as you cook. Combine
meat and onions with rest of ingredients and cook on low
heat
for at least an hour, adding the spice water (use a tea
strainer)
as it is needed.
This sauce may be frozen in pint containers and used as needed.
May be used over spaghetti
with
sprinkle
of Parmesan
cheese.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti and cook.
After training, run cold water of the pasta for a few minutes and set aside.
Cut into small pieces the cucumbers, peppers, and tomatoes.
Mix into the spaghetti and then add olives and 3/4 of the bottle of dressing and 1/2 bottle of Salad Supreme.
Chill for at least 2 hours and then serve. (Toss again before serving.)

title: creamy italian rice
directions: Bring broth, mushrooms and seasonings to boil in medium saucepan.
Stir in rice and cheese.
Cover.
Remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add soups and Cheez Whiz.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Fold in broccoli and rice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika or top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Can be halved or put into 2 casseroles to freeze one.
If freezing, do not top with cheese until ready to bake.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Beat, then spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and cut.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar together, add egg, milk and flavoring.
Blend in self-rising flour; mix thoroughly.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll out dough on floured pastry cloth or board to l/8-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cut into rounds of 2-l/2-inch. Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 400° for 6-9 mins.

title: mom's cucumber pickles
directions: *Use enough to make a creamy dressing to pour over cucumbers and onion rings.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all together and add Rice Krispies.
Mix well with hands and shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake well and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: colored popcorn
directions: Put corn in lightly buttered bowl.
Place sugar and water in saucepan to approximately 240° (medium boil until dissolved).
Add coloring at the end of the cooking and stir.
Pour over popcorn, stirring to coat evenly.
Keep stirring.
Add confectioners sugar and stir until kernels separate.

title: cow patty cookies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together.
Melt butter in sauce pan. Add cocoa, sugar, and milk.
Bring to a rolling hard boil for i minute.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and peanut butter, mix well.
Then add oats, slowly, stirring well.
Drop spoon size cookies on to waxed paper and let harden.

title: black magic cake(from an old hershey recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8-inch layer pans or one 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sift together all the dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Then add the wet ingredients.
Stir to blend. Then mix at medium speed for 2 minutes.
(Note:
The batter will be thin.)

title: salmon dinner
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover with buttered corn flakes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix graham crackers with 1 stick of butter.
Press into a large square dish.
Slice bananas on this.
Add well drained pineapple, 1/2 of the cherries and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Beat eggs and 1 stick melted butter for 15 minutes.
Add confectioners sugar and beat well.
Pour over other ingredients.
Add Cool Whip.
Add remainder of the nuts and cherries.

title: lemon sponge pies
directions: First beat
egg
whites until stiff; set aside.
Then I cream shortening;
add
sugar
and
egg yolks, lemon juice and rind. Add
milk,	then
sprinkle flour over the top and blend into liquid
mixture.
Last
of	all
add egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 40	to 45 minutes.	Check on them as I find sometimes they will brown more quickly.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, add rice, water and soups.
Stir, then lay chicken portions on rice and sprinkle with French onion soup mix.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: cranlets
directions: Mix cranberry sauce, sugar and gelatin together. Bring to a boil. Add the jellos and stir and cook for at least 5 minutes. Pour into 9 x 9 inch pan or glass dish. Cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate 12 hours. Cut into small 1/2 inch squares. Roll in sugar. Put on cookie sheet lined with wax paper. Leave air space around each piece. Let dry 24 hours. Roll again in sugar and return to cookie sheet. Repeat this every 24 hours until they stay dry. Do not refrigerate. Place in airtight container when dry.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Mix the above and pour over one pack of bones, skinless chicken breast. Pierce several times with a fork to allow marinade to penetrate chicken. Set aside at room temperature for at least 2 hours or up to 24 hours in the refrigerator. Grill, Broil, or Bake in 350 degrees until done about 20-25 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: To 1 carton whipping cream, add 2 packages Choco-bake and Carnation milk.
Blend on fast for at least 3 minutes.
Add sweetened condensed milk, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Blend 3 minutes.
Fill with sweet milk.

title: saucy cocktail franks
directions: Cut frankfurters crosswise into 3/4-inch pieces.
Place barbecue sauce in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in sugar, horseradish and mustard.
Microwave covered with lid at High power until sauce is hot, 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Add frankfurter pieces to sauce.
Stir to mix well.
Microwave covered at High power until frankfurters are hot throughout, 4 to 6 minutes.
Stir once or twice during cooking.
Transfer to heated serving bowl. Serve hot with cocktail picks.
Pass chips in separate bowl.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve each jello in 1 cup boiling water; add 1/2 cup cold water to each.
Place one flavor in refrigerator in lightly greased salad glass dish (13 1/2 x 8 3/4-inch).
Bring 2 cups of milk to a boil; add one cup of sugar and stir until dissolved.
Dissolve 2 packages of Knox gelatine in 2 cups cold water.
Add gelatin mixture to milk and sugar mixture.
Mix vanilla in sour cream.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Beat with mixer until well blended.
When mixture is fairly cold, measure 1 1/2 cups and spoon gently over first layer of jello.
Refrigerate until set.
When white layer is set, add another jello layer.
Continue to do this until you have completed the 7 layers.

title: lemon delight
directions: Sprinkle crushed honey granola cereal on cream cheese layer. Beat pudding, milk, and lemon juice until smooth.
Put on top of granola.
Spread Cool Whip on top of lemon pudding.

title: betty's easy oven fried chicken
directions: All ingredients are approximate and can be adjusted to your taste.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and let stand for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding food coloring with milk; blend well.
Makes 3 large layers.

title: ten minute peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and Karo in a 2-quart measuring bowl.
Cook in microwave oven on High for 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook 2 to 5 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes until syrup and peanuts are lightly browned.
Stir in oleo, vanilla and baking soda until light and foamy.
Spread to desired thickness on a lightly buttered cookie sheet.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together.
Gradually mix milk.
Beat egg yolks and a portion of milk.
Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour a small portion that is heated into beaten egg yolks.
Stir, then gradually add to chocolate portion.
Return to microwave.
Continue to cook for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring every 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until cooked to right consistency.
Add butter, then vanilla.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in condensed milk. Add salt. Remove from heat. Add walnuts and vanilla. Spread into foil lined 8-inch pan. Chill until firm. Cut in squares.

title: grandma's grape jello
directions: Mix together Jell-O, water, pie filling and pineapple.
Put in mold or nice dish.
Refrigerate until set. Add Cool Whip and nuts to top prior to serving.

title: bacon and chive potato salad
directions: Add potatoes to boiling water; cook 14 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard in large bowl.
Add potatoes, bacon and chives; mix lightly.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: layered tuna salad
directions: Layer lettuce, shells, cucumbers, tomatoes, tuna, peas and cheese into a 3-quart bowl.
Spread salad dressing or mayonnaise over salad.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight. Toss to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fat-free oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until bottoms are golden brown.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla in small mixer bowl until smooth (about 1 minute).
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake until golden brown, 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve warm with whipped cream of ice cream.

title: macaroni salmon salad
directions: Mix together and chill well.

title: peach fuzz
directions: Put in blender peaches and a few ice cubes until blended.
Add lemonade, vodka and water.
In off season, use 1 large can of peaches.

title: double-rich chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and cocoa powder.
Mix well with a wire whisk and set aside. In a large bowl, blend sugars with an electric mixer at medium speed.
Add butter and beat to form a grainy paste.
Scrape down sides of bowl, then add eggs and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until fully combined.
Add the flour mixture and chocolate chips and blend at low speed just until combined.
Do not overmix.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets, 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake for 18 to 22 minutes.
Immediately transfer cookies with a spatula to a cool surface.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: "big" chocolate chip cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a pizza pan.
In a large bowl, mix cake mix, eggs, oil and water.
Fold in chocolate chips. Spread onto pizza pan.

title: angel food and pudding dessert
directions: Break cake into pieces in baking dish.
Make pudding following directions on box.
Add pineapple; mix.
Pour over cake.
Top with Dream Whip and nuts.

title: cheese chunks
directions: Put cheese and margarine together in a bowl to soften while you prepare the bread.
Remove crusts from bread and cut into 16 large chunks, place chunks on a cookie sheet and put in the freezer for an hour or so, because they are easier to spread when they are frozen.
Now combine margarine and cheese spread, cream until smooth.
When ready, spread this mixture on all six sides of the bread chunks.
It's a messy job, so take off your rings first.
Put the cheesed bread back on the cookie sheet and back into the freezer until firm.

At this point, they can be dumped into a plastic bag and saved until needed or may be put directly in the oven without freezing the second time, but it's so messy that you won't want to do it at the last minute.
Bake at 375° until the edges are golden brown, about 10 minutes, but watch carefully, because it will burn easily.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil and cube potatoes (with or without jackets).
Mix the sour cream, onion, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Add butter and cheese.
Turn into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered or Pam sprayed baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mary raper's seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add ingredients by layers in the order given.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes. Let cool in pan before cutting into squares.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Combine spices and cook to soft boil.
Add 2 cups pecan halves.
Stir constantly until they are sugary.
Pour out on waxed paper and separate.

title: swiss egg casserole
directions: Place layer of eggs in buttered casserole.
Season with salt and pepper; sprinkle with crumbs.
Cover with layer of tomatoes; sprinkle with basil, salt, pepper, scallions and parsley.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used.
Combine beaten eggs with salt, cream and nutmeg in bowl.
Pour over layer in casserole. Place casserole in pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until custard is firm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Sieve berries; discard seeds.
Mix berries, limeade, 2 cups water and sugar.
Chill.
At serving time, add Sprite and ice. Makes 15 (4 ounce) servings.

title: spinach rice
directions: Coat a large saucepan with cooking spray.
Add oil.
Place over high heat until hot.
Add onion and saute 1 minute.
Add rice, water and spinach.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 13 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and spinach is thawed, breaking spinach apart with a fork. Stir in cheese, salt and nutmeg.
Yields 4 servings.
Serving size is 1 cup.

title: hot dog italiano
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large saucepan and simmer about 30 to 45 minutes, covered, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens.
Serve over cooked and drained rice while hot. Serves 4 to 8 people.

title: sausage and cheese biscuits
directions: Soften cheese and grate or buy already grated.
Mix with sausage and Bisquick.
There are no liquids, but it blends together very nicely.
Shape into bite sized biscuits.

title: eggplant chili
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Add all ingredients and cook over low heat, covered, for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with grated cheese sprinkled on top.

title: pioneer drumsticks(method:  stick)
directions: Put hot dog on a stick.
Wrap dough around the hot dog; put over coals to cook.
Serve with salad, vegetable, fruit and drink.

title: chili enchiladas
directions: Blend all ingredients except tortillas.
Spoon filling in tortilla and roll.
Spread remaining ingredients over top of tortillas and bake until hot and cheese is melted.

title: red cabbage
directions: Cut red cabbage into bite size pieces.
Add sugar, apple and salt.
Put into large saucepan, cover with boiling water and cook for 1 hour.
Then add vinegar and cook one more hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables together until done.
Put into a buttered casserole.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour celery soup over vegetables.
Sprinkle grated cheese over this; top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, or until cheese has melted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and onion in large pot for 1 1/2 hours. Remove chicken to cool and debone. Remove 2 cups of broth and set aside. Use broth and onion to boil noodles in. In large mixing bowl, put soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Mix and add deboned chicken and 2 cups broth. Boil noodles until tender. Drain noodles and add to chicken mixture. Mix well and salt and pepper to taste. Put in large baking dish. Slice Velveeta on top. Bake at 400° until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs, water and pumpkin to mixture.
Sift remaining ingredients (except nuts) and add to previous mixture.
Add nuts after mixing.

title: old recipe for excellent mincemeat
directions: Take 5 pounds of neck of beef and put to boil in enough water to cover the meat.
Take off the scum that rises when the water reaches the boiling point; add hot water from time to time until it is tender.

Then remove the lid from the pot and salt; let it boil until almost dry, turning the meat occasionally in the liquid. Take from fire and let stand overnight until thoroughly cold. Remove all bones, gristle or stringy bits; chop very fine, mincing at the time 3 pounds of beef suet, fresh.

title: delmer's peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish. Mix flour and sugar.
Stir in enough water to make batter.
Add peaches to melted butter in dish.
Pour batter around into peaches.
Stir a little to spread it around into peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until desired brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti 12 to 15 minutes and drain well.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Add Italian dressing and marinate for 24 hours.
Add chopped or cherry tomatoes prior to serving.

title: chili-mac
directions: In a large kettle, cook ground beef, onion and celery. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato juice, kidney beans and seasonings. Simmer on low heat 30 minutes. Prepare macaroni according to package directions. Drain. Stir macaroni into chili mixture. Heat through. Serve in warm bowls. Garnish with spoonful of sour cream and green onions. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and Pet milk together.
Add thawed Cool Whip.
Tear up angel food cake and put into punch bowl.
Fold over the sour cream and Cool Whip mixture onto angel food cake until well coated.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat.
Continue cooking until thick and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Mix with sliced potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef, add onions and cook until tender.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve on bun or french bread.

title: chocolate drops
directions: *Can use 1 1/2 packages of small marshmallows instead of the large marshmallows.

title: crab soup
directions: You will need a 4-gallon pot.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Make your favorite pie crust. Divide in half.
Roll out thin. Combine sugar, oleo and cinnamon. Sprinkle over each pie crust. Roll up and cut in 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Stand upright in loaf pan and sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and some cinnamon.
Mix the Pet milk and water and pour over top.
Bake at 350° or 375° until brown, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut bacon up into small bits and cook until they are crisp and light brown.
Then mix in onion and cook until light brown. When finished, set aside.
Mix barbecue sauce, brown sugar, catsup, Realemon, syrup and Worcestershire sauce until brown sugar is dissolved.
Add mixture of bacon and onions, mixing well.
Fold in beans, blending well.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.
Serves 8 - 10.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook all ingredients together except green beans and mushrooms until cabbage is tender.
Then add green beans and mushrooms with liquid.
Serves 8.
Each serving has 0 fat and only 36 calories.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix yeast with 2 tbsp. water. Stir with remaining ingredients and yeast mixture. Spoon into greased muffin pan and bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes. Cover and put remaining dough in the refrigerator.

title: cherry frappe
directions: Combine cherries, ice cream and half the sherbet in electric blender.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses half filled with crushed ice. Top with scoop of remaining sherbet. Garnish with mint. Serve with straws.
Blend half the ingredients at a time for easier handling.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in shallow casserole dish.
Add in layers, chili, relish and onion.
Top with shredded cheese. Heat in microwave for several minutes until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Serve warm with nachos.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread first 3 items in pan.
Top with fresh lettuce, tomatoes, green onions, shredded cheese and olives.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour and sour cream. Stir in bouillon granules, water and pepper. Set aside. In a large skillet cook and stir meat, mushrooms, onion and garlic in margarine until meat is done and onion are tender. Add sour cream mixture. Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly. Serve over noodles. Serves 4.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Cake:
In large bowl, mix together cake mix and strawberry jello; stir.
Add oil, 1 cup coconut, milk, 1 cup drained strawberries, 1 cup pecans and eggs, one at a time.
Pour into 3 greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken a la king
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Place in a slow cooker. In a medium bowl, stir soup, flour and pepper until blended.
Pour over chicken.
Do not stir.
Cover and cook on high for 2 1/2 hours or 5 to 5 1/2 hours.
Stir in peas, onions, pimiento and celery salt.
Cover and cook on high for 20 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fix-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in saucepan; add water to cover and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat to medium and simmer 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain.
Peel potatoes; place in a large mixing bowl and mash with a potato masher.
Add 2 tablespoons butter, cream cheese, sour cream, milk and salt, mixing until all ingredients are blended.
Spoon into lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
