Brush top of mixture with melted butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake immediately, or cover and refrigerate.
If refrigerated, let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Have macaroni cooking while preparing cheese sauce.
Cook and stir margarine, onion, salt and pepper in a 3-quart pot until onion is slightly tender.
Blend in flour, cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Stir in milk; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add cooked macaroni. Stir well.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Cook, uncovered, in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Should be slightly brown.
It's fun to slice up about 5 hot dogs and add to casserole before baking.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: In blender, mix onion, salt, garlic, garlic salt, dry mustard, paprika, sugar and vinegar.
Add salad oil.
Blend again.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 pint.

title: cucumber marmalade
directions: Peel and remove large seeds from cucumbers and finely chop enough to measure 2 cups.
In a large saucepan, combine cucumbers thoroughly with sugar, lime juice, lime rind and a few drops of green food coloring.
Bring mixture to a rolling boil and boil vigorously for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove mixture from heat and immediately stir in 1/2 bottle pectin.
Skim off the foam and stir for 5 minutes, skimming off any more foam.
Ladle into hot sterilized glass jars and seal immediately with melted paraffin. Serve with meat.

title: cheese and garlic biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead and cut like biscuits or drop mix from spoon.
Bake at 450 degrees for 8-10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: macaroni and cheese(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine macaroni, Cheddar cheese, onion and parsley.
In blender combine cottage cheese, milk and mustard.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over macaroni mixture and mix thoroughly.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Turn into a 2-quart casserole dish coated with nonstick spray. Crumble bread crumbs and Parmesan and sprinkle over casserole. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: skillet date cookies
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, butter, vanilla and dates in skillet over low heat and cook until dates are melted and thickened.
Let cool. Add pecans and cereal. Shape in small balls. Roll in coconut. Chill in airtight containers.
These freeze well or will keep for weeks in refrigerator. Serve straight from refrigerator or may be served at room temperature.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Cook sausage and onion until brown, drain. Mix other ingredients excluding cheese, put 1/2 in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread sausage over this, then cheese.
Add remaining mix and bake at 375° until brown.

title: creamed deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise into halves. Combine egg yolks with next 7 ingredients.
Beat together until well blended and smooth.
Fill whites with yolk mixture.
Pour sauce over the eggs in baking pan. Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add onion soup mix and water; cook 15 minutes.
Add seasonings and sugar and tomato sauce.
Add vegetables and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: old fashion lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans according to instructions.
Drain; reserve liquid. In saucepan combine onion, pepper and green onion.
Mix soup, liquid from beans and water (liquid and water should be 1/2 cup). Pour soup mixture over vegetables in saucepan.
Heat stirring. Blend sour cream, mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir into mushroom soup mixture.
Add cooked lima beans.
Pour mixture into 6-cup casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add flour, salt and sugar.
Add milk and flavoring.
Add butter and cook until thick.
Put in unbaked pie crust and brown.

title: nachos
directions: Spread bean dip on each tortilla chip.
Top with some cheese. Place 12 chips in a circle on a paper plate.
Cook for 1 minute or until cheese begins to melt.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler.
Add peanut butter, then add other.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool to harden. Yields 50 to 60 cookies.

title: bran muffins(microwave)
directions: In a 1 cup measure, heat water to boiling (1 minute).
Place bran cereal in bowl.
Stir in water until moistened.
Add butter and let set until softened.
Cover.
Stir in sugar and egg; beat well.
Blend in flour, soda and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Spoon into paper lined custard cups filling half full.
Store any remaining batter in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks, using from it as desired. This recipe is easily doubled.
Cook muffins uncovered until no doughy spots remain.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; mix lightly through apples.
Heap up in pastry-lined pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust which has slits cut in it.
Seal and flute.
Cover edge with 1/2-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until nicely browned and apples are cooked through.
Makes 9-inch pie.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine sugar, Jell-O and water in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Dissolve sugar and Jell-O. Remove from heat and stir in fruit, pineapple and apricots. Set aside to cool. Combine milk and cream cheese. Beat until it is smooth. Then stir in Jell-O mixture and nuts. Chill.

title: sombrero pie
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir meat and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except pastry.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare pastry.
Pour meat mixture into ungreased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inches).
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: green salad
directions: Pour cold water in bowl.
Sprinkle gelatine on top of water. Add sugar, salt and hot water and stir until dissolved.
Add vinegar and green coloring; cool.

When mixture begins to stiffen, add remaining ingredients. Pickles should be sliced thin, almonds chopped or cut in small pieces and pineapple cut in small pieces. Use molds that have been rinsed in cold water.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: chicken dumplins
directions: Boil chicken until done; let cool. Take off bone. Put chicken back into broth. Cut can biscuits into strips. Put in salt and pepper. Cook until done.

title: butter pecan pie
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix melted oleo with flour and nuts.
Mix together well and pat out in pie plate for crust.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°; let cool until cold.

title: those potatoes
directions: Layer in order listed.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes.
Whisk egg and water.
Combine flour, salt, pepper, paprika and crackers.
Dip tomato slice in egg wash, then coat both sides with flour mixture.
Place on wax paper to dry 15 minutes.
Heat oil in iron skillet.
Fry tomatoes in single layer until golden brown on both sides, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: wild rice and chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients adding some chicken broth so mixture isn't too dry.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered.

title: bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, pour 1 cup boiling water over 1 cup cereal and raisins. Let stand for 1 minute. Add flours, baking soda, pumpkin pie spice, salt and remaining cereal. In another bowl, beat eggs well. Add sugar, oil and vanilla. Mix cereal/raisin mixture, egg mixture and buttermilk. Stir well. Will be very stiff. Let sit at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring often. Mixture can be stored in covered container in the refrigerator for up to 3 weeks or bake right away. Spoon mix into greased muffin pan and bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Do not overbake. Yield: 3 to 4 dozen large muffins.

title: elegant meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into loaf.
Place in baking pan. Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes for easy slicing.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Add beaten egg yolks and Worcestershire sauce to cheese. Combine with beaten egg whites and fold in crushed potato chips. Bake in 400° oven until puffed and brown.
Serve at once.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time. Sift flour and soda together. Add one third of flour, then one half sour cream, another one third of flour, sour cream, etc. Add vanilla and lemon extract. Bake in tube pan one hour and 15 minutes or until done at 325°.

title: butterscotch sicles
directions: Mix pudding with liquids.
Pour into Dixie cups.
Freeze until just solid.
Add popsicle sticks.
Freeze again.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together to form 6 to 8 patties.
Cook in frying pan with small amount of oil for 4 minutes on each side. These are truly the best crab cakes I have ever had!

title: shrimp quiche
directions: Cook shrimp; drain.
Mix eggs, cream cheese, salt and pepper. Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add to egg mixture along with shrimp.
Reserve some shrimp for garnish.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil all ingredients, except corn and soda, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir in quickly and pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Put in large pan and place in oven.
Bake at 200° to 225° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in tightly closed containers.

title: pasta with shrimp
directions: Cook bacon pieces (not crisp); drain fat and set aside bacon. Saute garlic in a little butter.
Add tomatoes, wine and thyme. Cover and simmer for a few minutes.

title: turkey tacos
directions: Brown meat; drain any fat.
Add onion; brown.
Add seasonings. Cook about 5 minutes.

title: take a leek dressing
directions: Simmer celery and leeks in boiling water for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain, reserving 2 cups of the liquid.
Cook the onion in the butter over low heat until tender, but not brown. Mix bread and seasonings together.
Add celery , leeks, as much reserved liquid as you need to make moist, butter and onion.
Mix together with a fork.
Stuffs a 10 to 12 pound bird.

title: peanut soup - from costa rica
directions: Soften the peanut butter in a pan over low heat.
Gradually stir in milk, salt and pepper.
Chill.
Cold peanut soup for 8 people.

title: three cheese macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni to package directions; drain.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add Cheddar and Swiss cheeses; stir until melted.
Stir in grated cheese.
Mix macaroni with cheese sauce.
Pour into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with additional grated cheese, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top browns.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler.
Cool.
Beat egg and add chocolate mixture.
Add powdered sugar to mixture. Mix in nuts, marshmallows and coconut.
Form into rolls and roll in coconut.
Chill and slice.

title: lil smokies in a cloud(makes approximately 20)
directions: Slice rolled crescent rolls right from the can in 1/4-inch slices.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle rolls with sesame seed.
Top with a thin slice of Provolone cheese.
Place a Smokie in the middle and press down into dough.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until dough is brown.

title: chili
directions: In frying pan, add tomatoes, kidney beans (with juice), onions and peppers.
Cook over low heat.
While this is cooking, stir in hamburger.
Simmer over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: white coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix.
Heat milk, sugar and coconut extract, then cool.
Poke holes in cake and pour cooled mixture over cake. Spread Cool Whip on top of
cake and sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate.

title: waldorf health salad
directions: Lightly toss avocado, apples, dates, walnuts and sprouts.
Mix lemon juice and salt to make dressing.
Add to other ingredients and toss again.
Simple, sweet and refreshing.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: orient express
directions: Wash, dry and prick potatoes with a fork.
Bake or microwave until tender.
While potatoes are cooking, drain and flake salmon. Add soy sauce, lemon juice and Oriental sesame oil.
Toss and set aside.
Once potatoes are done, split open.
Squeeze gently to fluff.
Top with salmon mixture, dividing equally.
Sprinkle with snipped chives and red pepper mix.
Serves 2.

title: ralph's zesty salsa(yield: 6 to 7 cups)
directions: Open jalapeno. Remove seeds and membranes. Discard. Open can of olives and discard liquid. Chop vegetables and jalapeno peppers. Combine ingredients. Stir well. Add salt, cumin and hot sauce to taste!

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat eggs and baking powder together until stiff.
Add sugar a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Fold in crushed Ritz crackers and pecans.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool about 2 hours before serving.
Spread Cool Whip over pie.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple with juice to a boil.
Add jello and mix.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add whipped topping and buttermilk. Whisk until blended.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch container.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: super-easy black forest cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per package directions.
Make two 8-inch layers.
Let cake cool completely.

title: mom's fudge
directions: Melt marshmallows and water in double boiler.
Mix sugar, milk, oleo, salt and vanilla and bring to boil.
Boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips and vanilla.
Blend in marshmallow mixture and nuts. Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Remove wing tips and reserve for the soup pot.
Cut wings apart at joint.
Brown wings on both sides in oil.
Remove wings with a slotted spoon.
Pour off excess oil.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together working in butter and adding water to make soft dough.
Put in buttered pan and cover with remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in moderate oven.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Preheat to 350°.
Melt butter.
Add sugar and molasses.
Mix thoroughly.
Lightly beat egg.
Add to butter mixture.
Blend well.
Sift flour with spices, salt and baking soda.
Add to mixture.
Batter will be wet.
Layer sheet of foil on cookie sheet.
Drop by teaspoon on foil.
Bake until cookies start to darken (8 to 10 minutes).
Remove from oven.
While still soft, let cool on foil.

title: gypsy schnitzel(silver bowl winner)
directions: Pound meat until thin.
Seed peppers and julienne cut.
Saute peppers in heated oil.
Remove peppers to another plate.
Dip meat in flour, egg, and crumbs; saute meat on both sides until brown and cooked through.
Transfer to platter.
Pour off oil, leaving one teaspoon of drippings in pan; blend in cornstarch and beef broth.
Simmer.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add sauted peppers and sliced lemon.
Pour pepper sauce over meat.

title: karo crazy crunch
directions: Mix popped corn and nuts; put on large cookie sheet.
In a 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and syrup.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture turns a light caramel color.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Pour over corn and nuts.
Stir to coat well. Let dry.
Break apart and store in tightly covered container. Makes about 2 pounds.

title: "the best" raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill a few hours or best if chilled overnight.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat with pepper and onion.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Test with a knife.

title: chocolate doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and mix well.
Stir in sour milk in which the soda has been added.
Mix together and sift flour into the mixture.
Add vanilla.
Melt the chocolate and butter together. Add to the batter.
Chill overnight.
Roll out and fry in deep fat.
Dip in sugar.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit juice, little lemon juice and cream cheese.
Mix and serve on fruit cocktail and other fruit.

title: dave's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute sausage and chuck.
Drain grease.
Add onion, pepper, mushrooms and garlic until onion is clear, then add next 3 herbs. In large saucepot, put sausage mixture and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over vermicelli with garlic bread and salad.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Cut chicken or turkey in small pieces. Drain Veg-All and reserve liquid.
Mix cream soup with approximately 1/3 of Veg-All liquid.
Mix top 3 ingredients together.
Season.
Add mashed potatoes or cooked rice. Heat in a 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Evening:
To make bread, combine ingredients in a large bowl until well blended.
Put in a greased bowl.
Turn dough over once to grease top.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and let stay overnight in a warm place.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together.
Beat in egg, vanilla, flour, salt and soda.
Make small balls of dough.
Press down with floured fork.
Bake 4 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet in a 375° oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, sugar, vanilla, eggs and zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Divide between 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tester is clean after inserting.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine corned beef with all ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: swedish ham balls
directions: Combine brown sugar, vinegar, water and mustard.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Combine meats, crumbs, eggs and milk; mix well. Form into balls.
Place in casserole and pour first mixture over meatballs.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 270°, basting often.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Mix ingredients and stuff celery heart rib.
Leave smaller leaves on celery.

title: gumbo
directions: In a skillet sprayed with Pam or salad oil, fry on medium heat the okra, corn, onion and tomatoes.
This will fry up juicy. Continue cooking until it cooks down to almost dry.
(If you use frozen corn, boil instead of fry.)

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender. Combine broccoli with onions, soup, cheese, mayonnaise and eggs. Place in greased casserole dish. Cover with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stroganoff
directions: Lightly brown steaks in small amount of oil.
Set aside. Saute onion.
Add mushroom soup, sour cream, seasoning and steaks. Serve with cooked noodles.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cheese, and pour into dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake another 15 minutes.

title: summer vegetables with mozzarella
directions: In large skillet melt butter over medium heat.
Add ingredients, except tomato and cheese.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender, about 7 to 10 minutes. Add tomato wedges; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let stand until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mama's peanut butter candy
directions: Mix
well
the peanut butter, margarine, syrup, vanilla and salt.
Sift
confectioners
sugar.
Gradually
stir sugar into peanut butter mixture until smooth.
Nuts may be added at this point, if desired.
Put mixture in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan; place in fridge.
Chill;
cut
into
squares.
Makes
about 2 pounds of candy or 2 to 2 1/2 dozen squares.

title: aunt vera's peanut brittle
directions: Combine nuts, Karo, sugar, butter and salt in heavy skillet. Cook on high heat, being careful not to burn it.
Stir until dissolved, 15 or 20 minutes, until mixture spins a thread.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in soda and vanilla.
Cool on cookie sheet and break into pieces when cool.
Can be used with 1 cup peanuts and 1 cup pecans or with 2 cups pecans.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at
a time and beat well.
Add milk, then crushed vanilla wafers, pecans and coconut.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for one hour and 15 minutes.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk and lemonade well.
Add Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust.

title: creole seasoning mix
directions: Mix well, pour into a shaker and use as a seasoning on steak, pork, chicken, deer, rabbit.
Allow to marinate overnight on meat if desired.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Blend 1/3 cup sugar with 1 tablespoon cornstarch and add crushed pineapple.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and salt. Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Spread cooled pineapple mixture over bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Pour in cheese mixture
and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 50 minutes. Cool.

title: pecan bread
directions: Melt butter in large pot. Cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and flour, a little at a time. Add 1 1/2 cups nuts.
Mix and pour into pan. Add rest of nuts on top. Bake at 325° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: snow cream
directions: Mix all together and then enjoy.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all
ingredients and pour in a buttered 1 1/2 quart dish. Pour
juice
over
the top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cover the last 20 minutes.

title: chicken in a bag
directions: Mix all spices together in a small bowl.
Pour spices in a large brown paper bag and shake.
Add whole chicken to bag and shake well.
Tie end of bag with a twist tie.
Place bag in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with tie to the side.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, then 350° for 12 to 20 minutes.

title: fancy chicken puff pie
directions: In medium saucepan over medium-high heat, melt butter and saute shallots lightly.
Stir in flour until creamy.
Add broth and sherry slowly; heat until boiling and gravy is smooth.
Season to taste with nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in ham, chicken, asparagus and cream. Pour chicken mixture into ungreased 9-inch pie plate.

title: graham-nut crust
directions: Microwave butter 45 seconds to melt.
Add crumbs, sugar and nuts.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Microwave 2 to 2 1/2 minutes, turning dish every 30 seconds.

title: meme's paute
directions: In skillet, brown your ground beef with the onion, chopped small, and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Make mashed potatoes with your milk and butter and put aside.
Take a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour ground beef at bottom, layer corn on top of beef, then potatoes.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Place milk in top of a double boiler.
Just as the water in the bottom of the boiler begins to boil, add cheese to milk.
When it starts to thicken, remove from heat.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: quick corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: baked beans
directions: Empty pork and beans into large casserole dish.
Add catsup, brown sugar and 1 can French fried onions.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Top with other can of French fried onions and bake for additional 5 minutes.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in one large salad in order given. Mix mayo with sugar and seasoned salt.
Spread over all.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon pieces on top.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: never fail roast
directions: Chop garlic; mix with salt and pepper.
Cut several holes in roast and stuff with garlic.
Place roast in Dutch oven size pot. Heat oven to 450° to 475°.
Roast without lid on 30 minutes to brown.
Add 2-inches water to bottom of pot.
Cover with lid and lower oven to 275° to 300° for 2 1/2 undisturbed hours.

title: rise and shine rolls(makes 12 rolls)
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve 2 cups flour, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt.
Heat sour cream, water and butter until very warm (120° to 130°).
Stir into dry ingredients.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix well and chill until ready to serve.

title: golden glow salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, saving the juice.
Add lemon juice to make 1 cup.
Stir into gelatin.
Chill until slightly set, then stir in pineapple and carrots in.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg, apples and nuts.
Sift in flour, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix well.
Spread in a 10 x 10-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.
Enjoy!

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in salad bowl and toss lightly.
Chill until ready to serve.
Better when it is a day old.

title: crazy chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken and discard.
Rinse chicken and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Mix together all the ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken salad for 25
directions: Mix and chill. (Frozen peas may be added.)

title: vegetable cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour.
Over medium heat, add milk to butter and flour, stirring with whisk until it thickens.
Remove from heat and add cheese; cover until cheese melts.
Great on vegetables, potatoes or rice.
Enjoy!

title: connie's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar; add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk; add flavoring and beat well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: crisp bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers into paper thin slices leaving peel on.
Slice onion into thin rings.
Dissolve salt in water and pour over the sliced vegetables.
Put about 1 quart crushed ice on top.
The ice and salt are what makes the pickles crisp.
Let stand 3 hours weighted down with a plate.
Drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices and bring to a boil.
Add drained vegetables and heat to boiling point.
Do not boil.
Pack in sterilized jars; fill to overflowing.
Seal.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt peanut butter and margarine over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until blended.
Spread in pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool; cut into squares.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Put in casserole dish.
Put slice of cheese on each piece of chicken.
Mix soup with 1 can of water; stir well.
Pour over chicken; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is well done.
Sprinkle dressing over top and bake for 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: fried squash
directions: In 1-gallon Ziploc bag, place all ingredients and shake. Fry until brown on each side.

title: licorice snaps
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake on ungreased pan at 375° for 9-12 minutes.

title: fattigman
directions: Beat egg yolks, whites, salt and sugar together for 1/2 hour. Add cream and cardamon; stir well.	Add butter, extract and brandy;
blend
well.
Mix	in
flour
thoroughly.	Dough should be	stiff
enough
to roll out very thin.
Refrigerate overnight. Roll
small
amounts of dough very thin.
Cut into rectangles. Shape
into
bows.	Deep fry at 365° until golden brown.

title: layered salad
directions: Break lettuce in a large flat bottom dish. Layer onions and cucumber over lettuce. Drain peas and layer over salad. Slice boiled eggs and layer on top. Mix mayonnaise and sugar. Layer over eggs. Sprinkle top with bacon bits and shredded cheese.

title: clams ala bonita
directions: Saute onion in oil until golden.
Then add minced clams and juice to sauteed mixture.
Remove from heat; add bread crumbs. Let stand 5 minutes (mixture will have thickened) and add grated cheese.
Fill clam shells; sprinkle with paprika and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: pear pie
directions: Put pears in crust, heaping in the middle.
Mix flour and sugar together; sprinkle over pears.
Cut butter in pats and put on sugar.
Sprinkle apple spice over the top.
It will be almost solid brown.
Put crust on top.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cover edges of crust if it starts to get too brown with foil.

title: puree of sweet potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes (in skins after washing) at 400° for 50 minutes, or until tender.
Peel and mash with butter and rum.
Stir in ginger.
Turn into saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring frequently to let most of the moisture evaporate from potatoes. Stir in cream.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: harvest loaf cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir together flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg, ginger and cloves. Add butter mixture alternately with dry ingredients, beating well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool cake.
Drizzle glaze over cake.

title: cranberry bars
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, oats, brown sugar, peel and baking soda.
Stir in melted margarine and mix thoroughly. Reserve 1 big cup of flour and oat mixture for topping.
Place remaining mixture in an ungreased 12 x 7-inch or little larger pan.
Press down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Carefully spread cranberry sauce on baked crust.
Stir nuts into remaining oat mixture and spread over cranberry sauce; pat down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes more.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: make ahead hamburgers
directions: Cook hamburger until it loses its color.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour off excess grease; cool.
Add cheese, onion, catsup and salad dressing.
Blend all together with cooled meat and pack in oblong baking dish.
Refrigerate.
Cut in squares, put on bun half and broil approximately 7 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oatmeal; add chips, nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Cook on low heat.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles (optional).

title: apple butter(jelly)
directions: Add spices to applesauce and boil.
Add Sure-Jell and sugar and boil 2 to 3 minutes until thick.
Put in jars and store in refrigerator.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain fat.
Add a little water.
Add taco seasoning.
Add refried beans.
Mix and add sliced olives.
Add onion if needed.
Mix evenly and put in casserole dish.
Spread sour cream.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake until melts.
Serve over chips.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti.
Cook ground beef about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Ricotta cheese.
Add next 5 ingredients and half of the spaghetti sauce and add ziti.
Pour in pan.
Top with remaining sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: low-fat fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar and pie filling.
Then add all other fruits and mix well.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: best ever pound cake
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt in a bowl; set aside. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, 1 at a time. Alternate with flour mix. Add vanilla. Add sour cream only until mixed. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: scones *
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease large baking sheet.
Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in dried fruit.
Combine milk and egg.
Mix into dry ingredients.
Gather dough into ball.
Roll dough out to 1/2-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut into 2 1/2 to 3-inch rounds.
Gather scraps, re-roll and cut out additional rounds.
Arrange on baking sheet, spacing 1/2 inch apart.
Bake until firm to touch, about 20 minutes.
Serve warm or room temperature.
Really cute for a buffet if you make mini-size scones, about 1-inch.

title: cinnamon-raisin muffins
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan sections two-thirds full and bake in preheated hot oven at 400° about 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: double cheese broccoli
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs. Place in greased casserole. Top with bread crumbs. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Flour your surface and rolling pin.
Roll out each biscuit until thin.
Mix applesauce and enough cinnamon to taste.
In the middle of each rolled biscuit put 1 to 2 tablespoons of applesauce mixture.
Then fold over one side of the biscuit and overlap the other side.
Flatten all sides with the tip of the fork.
In a nonstick pan, melt 1 to 2 tablespoons of butter and place biscuits in butter.
Brown on both sides.
Remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: oven smoked turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Fill cavity of turkey with celery stalks for moisture.
Place in large cooker.
Baste with a sauce of equal parts honey and lemon juice.
Add hickory chips that have been saturated with water for a hickory smoked flavor.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend together ingredients except cheese and potato chips. Put in greased 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese then potato chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until cheese is delicately browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: one-bowl banana bread
directions: Put all but last 2 ingredients in mixer bowl, beat until creamy.
Add walnuts and dates.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes for 2 small loaves, or 1 loaf at 350° for 55 minutes.
Very easy to make.

title: goat cheese alfredo sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and process until smooth. Pour into small saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until hot. (Do not boil as mixture will separate.) If it separates, return to blender and reprocess. Yield: 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer baking pan in order of ingredients listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a large Dutch oven, saute sausage until lightly browned. Remove from pot.
Saute onion, bell pepper, celery, green onions and garlic in meat drippings until tender.
Add tomatoes, thyme, peppers and salt.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Melt butter and mix with package of Pepperidge Farm mix.
Put half of stuffing mix in a baking dish.
Put squash mix in the middle.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: yam casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole dish. Spread topping over the top of mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Put layer of graham crackers in dish; moisten with butter. Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese until smooth.
Layer this mixture on crackers, then layer of cherry pie filling.
Repeat this starting with graham crackers until all ingredients are gone.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend together flour and salt; stir in.
Roll dough into balls.
Beat egg white slightly with fork.
Dip balls in egg white.
Roll in nuts.
Place about 1 1/4-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet. Press thumb gently in center of each.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Fill thumb prints with jelly or tinted icing. Makes 3 dozen.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, cream of tartar, cold water, and salt in top of double boiler.
Beat 1 minute, cook over boiling water.
Beating constantly until mixture forms peaks (about 7 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and beat until frosting is of spreading consistency.
To make chocolate frosting, melt 2 squares of chocolate and gently stir in and then cool.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix and put in baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake until hot through.

title: caramel layered brownies
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Set aside. Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, butter and nuts.
Stir by hand until mixture holds together.
Put 1/2 of this into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(For best consistency, place dish in shallow pan of water while baking.)

title: frito fried fish
directions: Crush Fritos in plastic bag.
Remove Fritos chips to bowl.
In bag, mix flour, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs in second bowl.
Drop fish in bag and shake.
Dip fish in beaten eggs.
Roll in crushed Fritos chips.
Fry in hot oil.

title: quick rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water; add sugar and salt with 1/2 the
flour.
Put in beaten egg and melted shortening.
Mix well and
add the rest of the flour.
Cover and let rise until double in	bulk.
Put
in	greased muffin pans or make into 12 rolls. Let it rise.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: miracle soup
directions: Cut up first 5 ingredients into bite-sized pieces.
Cover with water and bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and onion soup and cook until desired tenderness (approximately 1 hour). Yield:
6 servings.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: In small bowl, combine oatmeal and water.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and then oatmeal.

title: chili for hamburgs
directions: Brown hamburg and Crisco in saucepan.
Drain grease.
Add water to beef.
Mix tomato soup, ketchup, chili powder, baking soda, salt, pepper and sugar.
Add to beef.
Boil until thickened. If not thick, thicken with flour mixed with water or bread crumbs.

title: joyce's blueberry dream dessert
directions: Break cake into pieces (about 1-inch in size).
Spread over bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Mix cream cheese and milk; pour over cake.
Spread pie filling over this.
Top with a layer of Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: briami - greek vegetable casserole
directions: Cut eggplant, zucchini and potatoes in bite-size chunks (do not peel zucchini or eggplant).
Slice peppers, onions and dice tomatoes.
Saute the vegetables, except tomatoes, in olive oil. Place sauteed vegetables in baking dish.
Add tomatoes into the pan to saute with crushed garlic.
Add sugar, salt and pepper and simmer for another minute.
Pour tomato sauce on top of the vegetables and bake at 350° until the vegetables are tender.

title: stuffed mushrooms with spinach
directions: Put spinach in 1/4 cup water; boil, then reduce heat to medium and cook spinach, covered, 10 minutes. Stir; remove from heat and drain. Remove stems from mushrooms. Arrange caps in a buttered (2 tablespoons) 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Finely chop stems. Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a saucepan and mix onion and garlic. Cook 5 minutes or until tender, then mix in bacon, spinach, chopped mushroom stems and heavy cream. Bring cream to a boil. Remove from heat and mix in Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper. Stuff mushroom caps generously with the mixture. Drizzle with 2 tablespoons melted butter. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, until lightly browned. Makes 12 servings.

title: dressing
directions: Mix and pour over salad; store extra in glass jar in refrigerator.
Good on cole slaw and macaroni salad.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour into pan the hash browns, melted butter, salt, pepper, chopped onion, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and Cheddar cheese and stir together.
Mix 1 1/2 cups corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter and sprinkle on top of potatoes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marinated pork strips
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Add pork strips, tossing to coat.
Cover; refrigerate for 2 hours.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup marinade, sesame seed and mustard.
Pour over pork strips; toss to coat.
Place in a single layer on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, turning once. Makes 4 main dish servings or 8 appetizer servings.

title: boston cream pie
directions: Cream margarine, vanilla and sugar well.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat in alternately with milk.
Pour into a greased 9-inch round pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: homemade tomato soup
directions: Chop celery and onion very fine; put in large stockpot.
Cook for 5 minutes and then add cream cheese.
Cook over a low heat until cream cheese is melted.
Add stewed tomatoes and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly so mixture does not scorch.
After tomatoes have cooked down into smaller pieces, and your mixture is very thick, slowly add milk to the consistency you prefer your soup.
Add tomato juice.
Next, salt and pepper to taste, and cook over a low heat for 1/2 hour (adding milk if the soup gets too thick).

title: chinese foo yong
directions: Combine lettuce, bean sprouts, chestnuts, bacon and eggs in salad bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dressing is made from last 6 ingredients.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Slice carefully in perfect halves and bake them for about 40 to 50 minutes until they are tender. Remove them from the oven and lower it. With a spoon, carefully scoop out the pulp or insides of the potatoes and put the pulp into a large bowl. Make sure the skins of the sweet potatoes remain intact. Mash the pulp with the help of a masher. Add and mix the rest of the ingredients well. Fill the sweet potato shells evenly with the pulp mixture. Put the potatoes in a buttered flat baking dish and dot each half with a bit of butter. Place them in the oven and bake for about 25 to 30 minutes. (The potatoes are done when they burn brown on top.)

title: peanut butter snacks
directions: Heat chips and peanut butter over hot water until melted.
Add the chow mein noodles and stir to cook.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on buttered cookie sheet and chill.
If desired, top with candied cherries.

title: golden punch(serves 75)
directions: Combine all juices in order given and pour over ice.
Add ginger ale and sparkling water just before serving.
Garnish with cherries, frozen in ice cubes.

title: white and black bean salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: apple and sausage stuffing
directions: In a large skillet, fry sausage and bacon until crisp and brown.
Remove sausages and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Replace in skillet and add onion, celery, mushrooms, apples, parsley and herbs.
Saute, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Stir in bread cubes and broth.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Stuff chicken or turkey and bake or put in a pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato salad with mint and spring onions(tamatar salat)
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut into thin wedges.
Finely slice spring onions and chop mint leaves.
Mix lemon juice, salt, sugar and chili powder together.
Stir until sugar dissolves, then pour over the combined ingredients and mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Cover and chill until serving time.

title: katie's peanut butter swirl
directions: Peel and cook potato.
Cream potato and add powdered sugar until mixture is stiff.
Roll out potato mixture on flat surface covered with a small amount of powdered sugar to keep from sticking.
Spread with peanut butter, roll up like a jelly roll and slice candy.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, lay Twinkies, side by side (cream side up) in two rows; spread with pineapple.
Cover with bananas. Prepare pudding according to package directions.
When thickened, spread over bananas.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, top with whipped topping and sprinkle with nuts.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into oblong thin patties.
Brown on both sides in skillet.
Remove meat and add 1 heaping tablespoonful flour to fat and brown.
Add enough water to make thin gravy.
Pour over steaks in a casserole dish or Dutch oven and bake at 350° until meat is tender and gravy is rich and thick.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in cold water, enough to cover chicken.
Add salt, pepper and celery leaves.
Cover tightly and bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer until chicken is done and tender.

title: savory pull-apart bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly spray square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches, with cooking spray.
Cover dried tomatoes with boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes; drain.
Finely chop tomatoes.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Combine flour, salt, soda and nutmeg.
Stir half the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture, then the zucchini (batter may look curdled). Add the remaining dry ingredients, then the nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: maple glazed chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients (except chicken) together and cook until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat and let cool.

title: mozzarella dip
directions: Dump all ingredients in blender, except Mozzarella cheese, and blend.
Add Mozzarella cheese and stir.
Ready to eat. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: special k meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a very large bowl, adding cereal last.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking pan lightly sprayed with Pam.
Mixture will be thick.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May freeze before baking for later use.
This recipe contains 1/3 egg per serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: oscar's cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in a hot greased skillet.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marvelous meat loaf
directions: In small bowl mix together tomatoes, carrots and celery, set aside.

title: steak fingers
directions: Trim any fat from steak.
Pound steak to 1/8-inch thickness, using a meat mallet, and cut into 4 x 1-inch strips.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
When ready to serve, add ice.
Serves 100 people.

title: onion corn bread muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and drippings.
Mix into batter.
Pour into greased muffin tins (8 count).
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: brunch pizza squares
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough into a greased pan (13 x 9 x 2 in.). Press dough 1/2 in up the sides.
Sprinkle with meat.
In a bowl, mix the other ingredients and pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered at 400°F for 15 min. or until crust is golden brown and cheese is melted.
About 8 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder, sugar and salt, mixing well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add cornmeal mix, stirring well.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon batter into a well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: adam's sunday brunch eggs for 4
directions: Spray top of double boiler with Pam.
Melt enough Velveeta to cover bottom of pan.
Scramble eggs with milk, salt, pepper and any of the following: Worcestershire sauce, bits of ham, onions, green pepper, pimiento, mushrooms, black olives, etc.
Pour into cheese and cook, stirring frequently, until eggs are cooked, but moist.

title: spiced wassail
directions: Simmer 10 minutes, covered.

title: special baked potato topping
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Serve with baked potatoes. Makes enough for 6.

title: chinese chicken with almonds
directions: Heat oil in wok or 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Add chicken; stir-fry about 5 minutes or until no longer pink in center.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, celery and mushrooms; stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through.
Stir in broth and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 6 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water; stir into chicken mixture.
Cook and stir about 30 seconds or until thickened.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Yields 6 servings.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant in half; scoop out and chop some of the pulp. Heat oil in skillet; add eggplant pieces, beef, onion, pepper, garlic, Tabasco and salt.
Saute until eggplant is lightly brown. Toss with rice to blend all ingredients.

title: sugar free fresh apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Prepare pie crust for 9 inch pie.

title: meat pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook until meat is brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in dish, covered with pie crust. Place crust on top after filling dish with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Pillsbury's already pie crust is best!

title: dill dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well and refrigerate.
Serve with fresh cut up vegetables.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cover chopped dates with 1 cup hot water. Set aside.
Cream the butter and sugar together. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add dates and water. Sift together flour, cocoa and baking soda. Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Pour batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chocolate chips and chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pork ribs and sauerkraut
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In roast pan, put salt and pepper on ribs.
Cut up onion and garlic.
Add to ribs.
Stir in water and bake until ribs are done.
Pour sauerkraut over ribs and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on each side.
While browning, mix mushroom soup, sour cream, onion, milk, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Set aside.
Peel and slice the potatoes.
Layer bottom of pan and pour 3/4 of the soup mixture over them.
Spread evenly.
Layer browned pork chops on top of potatoes.
Spoon remaining soup mixture on each chop.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: party punch
directions: Mix the punch, lemonade and orange juice.
Stir in the Sprite or 7-Up.

title: italian egg biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, sift first 4 ingredients together.
Make a well and add shortening, milk, eggs and vanilla.

Mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes; be careful not to burn the bottoms. When slightly cooled, ice with desired frosting and sprinkle with colored sugars.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry-lined pie pan. With rotary beater, blend remaining ingredients; pour into pie pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: chewy cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake in a greased pan at 300° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening; add mashed bananas.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done (when toothpick comes out clean).

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix.
Add salt and pepper for taste.
Good to let set overnight.
Lets flavors set.
Keeps 4 to 5 days.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef until browned.
Pour off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until thickened.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and cook broccoli 1 minute.
Combine ingredients except cheese.
Pour into greased casserole and top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: slush
directions: Boil together and cool the water and sugar to make syrup.
Add rest of ingredients, including vodka.
Freeze in large non-metal container at least 24 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Fill drink glass 3/4 full and then add bottled Squirt to glass to fill.
May be kept indefinitely in freezer, but stir it once in a while.

title: jan's caramel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

Mix cake mix and next 3 ingredients. Beat 2 minutes. Grease and flour two 8-inch round pans or 9 x 13 oblong pan. Pour batter into pan(s). Tap the pans a few times on the counter to remove bubbles in batter. Cook for 22 to 25 minutes. Cool completely. When done, ice with Caramel Icing.

title: wedding punch
directions: Combine juices and water in a large punch bowl; mix well. Right before serving, add ginger ale, sparkling water and white grape juice.
Stir to blend.
Garnish glasses with fresh strawberries and a sprig of mint.
(Freeze some of juice mixture in a pretty mold to keep punch cool without diluting flavors.)
Yield: About 50 (4 ounce) servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse mushrooms and break off stems. Chop stems and set aside.
Melt 3 tablespoons of butter in skillet; saute bottoms of caps for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove and place in baking pan.
Heat rest of butter and saute stems, green peppers and onion until soft, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in bread, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fill each cap with mixture.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in broiler with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Combine all other ingredients in Teflon pan and mix well.
Add browned chicken and cook for 40 to 45 minutes covered.

title: overnight butterscotch rolls
directions: Place 1/2 of frozen rolls in angel food or Bundt cake pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 of the nuts and dry pudding mix.
Place remaining rolls in the pan distributed evenly.
Sprinkle with the rest of nuts and pudding mix.
Pour margarine over rolls.
Place in cold oven and leave overnight.
Next morning bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry fluff salad
directions: Mix 1 cup hot water, 1/2 cup cold water and 1/2 cup pineapple juice with jello.
Let jello partially set.
Mix sugar and cream cheese together.
Mix remainder of ingredients with the cream cheese.
Add jello and let it set.

title: cheese spread
directions: Drain the pimientos and chop finely (or mash them with the back of a fork).
Combine the 3 cheeses in a large mixing bowl and mix well.
Add the pimientos, pecans, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well and shape into 2 balls.
Sprinkle the chili powder, paprika and cayenne pepper on waxed paper or plastic wrap. Roll each ball in the spices until completely covered and refrigerate or freeze.

title: refrigerator dill pickles
directions: Use 1 clean glass gallon jar with a lid.
Pack cucumbers whole on ice chunks (or quarters) in jar.
Add garlic and dill weed to jar of cucumbers.
Bring water, vinegar and canning salt to a boil. Pour boiling hot over cucumbers and weigh cucumbers down so brine covers.
Store on counter for 7 days.
Cover; then refrigerate.

title: port apple butter
directions: Heat water and wine to boiling in a large kettle.
Add apples and cook slowly 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until mixture begins to thicken. Beat with an electric mixer to break up apple slices.
Add sugar, salt and spices.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until thick. (This last cooking should take about 1 hour.)

title: orange-tapioca jello
directions: Combine tapioca pudding, Jell-O and juice.
Heat mixture until it becomes clear and thick.
Cool until set.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Garnish with fresh orange slices.
Serve chilled.

title: caster oil cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Use enough flour to make a dough that can be rolled out.
Cut and bake in hot oven.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add to sweet potatoes.
Mix milk and eggs together.
Add to sweet potato mixture.
Pour filling into pastry lined pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued brisket of beef
directions: Sprinkle the brisket with all 3 of the salts and the liquid smoke. Let soak overnight, turning once or twice. Wrap in heavy-duty foil and bake 5 hours at 275°. Let cool and slice thin. Cover with Barbecue Sauce and heat for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix the ingredients; let melt and add 1 can coconut and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 250° to 300° until golden brown.

title: bacon and egg casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, then break up.
For sauce cook onion in butter, flour and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add Cheddar cheese and stir until melted.
Layer in casserole 6 eggs, half of the sauce, 1 1/2 cups chips and 1 pound bacon.
Repeat layers.
Cook for 45 minutes in 300° oven.

title: mamie's beefy skillet
directions: Brown the chuck and drain off the grease.
Cook the macaroni until done, add to meat mixture.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook until desired consistency.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream
margarine
and
cream cheese.
Add sugar slowly. Add 2 eggs and beat well.
Add flour and 1 egg at a time until all the flour
and	eggs have been added.
Cook in large cake pan 1 1/2 hours
at
This
makes a layer cake and will stay moist until last piece is gone.

title: crawfish puffs
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks, milk and oil until blended.
Add to dry ingredients and beat until blended.
Stir in crawfish, rice, pepper and onions.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in batter.
Add pepper to taste.
Drop batter from tablespoon into fat.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; beat until light.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to egg mixture and blend until smooth.
Add the rest of the ingredients, except the cream cheese, and mix well. Spoon into 2 (9x5 inch) greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove from pans immediately. Cool.
Serve with whipped cream cheese (optional).

title: cinnamon pound cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil, milk and sour cream. Set aside.
Mix together sugars, cinnamon and nuts.
Put half of the cake mixture in a greased Bundt pan.
Then put half of the sugar mixture on top of this.
Put rest of the cake mix on top and then remainder of sugar mixture.
Cut sugar mixture in.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Boil noodles until tender in boiling water.
Drain.
Toss with cream, butter and cheese until completely melted.
Serve at once.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In deep kettle, put in oil, onions, water and bouillon cubes; cook until boiling slightly.
Then add noodles, broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook until noodles and broccoli are tender (about 15 minutes).
Mix 3 cups cold milk with flour.
Mix other 3 cups milk with melted Velveeta cheese.
Add both milk mixtures to kettle; cook until just comes to boiling so soup will thicken some.

title: canned strawberries
directions: Clean and chop berries as for shortcake or fresh use.
Mix sugar, Clear Jell, Kool-Aid and salt together.
Mix well.
Add to strawberries and mix together.
Put in jars and cold pack for 10 minutes.

title: guacamole salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve over salad greens.

title: watergate cake
directions: Prepare cake from first 5 ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup chopped walnuts to batter.
Bake in an oiled and floured pan for 45 minutes, or until done.
Cool completely.

title: abby's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baked pie shell. Bake 45
to 50 minutes in a 350° oven. Top with whipped cream or ice cream as you wish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take off bone. Use 1/2 of chicken broth and add 1 diced bell pepper, 1 small chopped onion and spaghetti. Cook noodles until done and drain. Using other

portion of broth to equal 1 can of cream of chicken soup and mix to spaghetti. Put half of spaghetti in 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Sprinkle Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese on top of spaghetti. Put remaining half of spaghetti on top of cheese and sprinkle more of the cheeses on top of spaghetti. Put in oven until cheese has melted.

title: franci's famous cheesecake
directions: Prepare your favorite graham cracker crust in a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large bowl beat cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, eggs (one at a time) and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool for 5 minutes on counter away from any draft.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in large punch bowl.
Add sherbet; serve as it melts.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add corn to egg yolks.
Beat egg whites with sugar.
Fold into other ingredients.
Cook in pan of water in oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken caruso
directions: Season chicken.
Saute in butter for about 2 minutes.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and Italian seasoning.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Add celery; cook until tender-crisp.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Salt chicken with the 2 teaspoons salt.
Cover with water. Cook until tender; debone chicken.
Put bread crumbs, seasoning, onions and celery in 11 x 14-inch baking dish.
Pour broth over. You may need to add 1 can chicken broth or some water and 1/2 cup butter.
Mix well.
Have dressing the consistency of cornbread. Add chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, eggs, celery, onion and pickle relish. Blend salad dressing and mustard.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Mix well with potatoes until well coated.
Serve when cold.
You can garnish potato salad with eggs in green pepper rings.

title: blessed and preserved children
directions: Blend together and mix well the children, puppies, kittens and butterflies.
Add them to the field, stirring constantly.
Every so often fold in the oak trees and sprinkle in bouquets of flowers.
Pour the brook over the pebbles and layer the edges with the sand.
Sift in the gentle breeze.
Spread over all the deep blue sky dropping in occasionally the rounded tablespoons of fluffy white clouds.
Bake in the sunshine on a nice warm day. The giggles and grins will surface to the top throughout processing time.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 4 tablespoons of cold water.
Add the boiling water, sugar, pineapple and lemon juice.
Chill about 15 minutes or longer until cool or mixture begins to congeal slightly.
Tear cake into small pieces.

title: rice crispie treats
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add liquids.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
This cake can be mixed and baked in the same pan, if desired.

title: vegetable chili
directions: In Dutch oven, saute zucchini, peppers, onions, celery, carrots and garlic.
Stir in tomatoes, picante, water, bouillon and cumin. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in olives, chili beans and garbanzo beans; simmer until thoroughly heated.

title: spicy cranberry warmer
directions: Place first 3 items in double thickness of cheesecloth.
Bring up corners and tie with a string.
Place with cider in large saucepan, or place loose spices in saucepan and strain before serving.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar; simmer 5 minutes.
Add cranberry juice and heat to simmering temperature. Serve hot in mugs.
Garnish with cinnamon sticks, if desired. This makes a nice beverage to serve at the holiday season.

title: double peanut clusters
directions: Combine peanut butter and chocolate chips in top of double boiler and place over hot (not boiling) water.
Over low heat, melt chips and peanut butter.
Add peanuts and stir until well coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper-lined cookie sheet. Chill until set.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine
oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat well. Add flour and beat well. Add remaining ingredients and stir. Put batter into a greased
and
floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy candy
directions: Mix margarine with crumbs, sugar, coconut, peanut butter and nuts.
Shape into small balls.
In top of double boiler melt chocolate bits and wax.
Dip balls into mixture to completely cover.
Lay on wax paper to chill.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix together the eggs, sugar, salt, nutmeg, milk and vanilla. Pour into deep 10-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Lower heat to 325° and bake 35 minutes more.
Test with knife blade in center.
If it comes out clean, pie is done.

title: company chicken
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken breasts.
Place in buttered baking pan and cover with cream of mushroom soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: easy oven squash
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in bowl.
Beat slightly egg and milk. Dip squash slices in the egg and milk.
Roll in the dry mix until coated.
Pour oil in heavy baking pan.
Place coated squash in pan.
Bake at 450° until brown, both sides.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix ingredients and let set 1/2 hour.
Just before serving, add Salad Supreme seasoning and toss well.
Serve.
You can add sliced fresh mushrooms, pepperoni and julienne strip cheese.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Bake half the batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix the caramels with the margarine and milk. Stir over low heat until melted.
Pour the caramel mixture over the baked cake.
Add the chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour the remaining batter on top and bake 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.

title: monkey bread(berryville bed and breakfast)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Grease or spray 12-inch Bundt pan.
Into pan, place pecans.
Melt together butter and brown sugar in small saucepan. In plastic bag or container with top, mix sugar and cinnamon. Unwrap biscuits.
Cut into quarters.
Put biscuit pieces in white sugar mixture and shake until coated.
Do this in small batches. Place coated biscuits into pan on top of pecans.
Pour brown sugar mix over all.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Invert onto serving dish and serve warm.
Enjoy!

title: cranberry chicken(healthy choice; serves 8)
directions: In a large bowl, stir onion soup mix into cranberry sauce. Pour dressing in (a little at a time) until well blended.
Spoon mixture over chicken laid out in a single layer in pan until well coated.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Baste every 15 minutes for better flavoring.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes until coating becomes caramelized.
(Can be marinated overnight, if desired.)

title: hot fruited tea punch
directions: Tie cinnamon sticks and cloves in a cheesecloth bag.
Combine spice bag, 1 quart water and tea bags in
a stockpot.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 30 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Remove tea bags, squeezing gently. Add remaining 4 quarts water, cranberry-apple drink and remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until sugar dissolves; stir occasionally.
Serve warm.
Yields 2 1/2 gallons.

title: crunchy cheese balls
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and pour in a shallow baking dish. Slice potatoes and boil until done but still firm.
Layer the potatoes over the ground beef.
Next, spread mushroom soup over the other ingredients.
(Can be added before the potatoes.) Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over the top of the casserole. Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: sunkist lemon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 1 egg, butter and dry cake mix until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture lightly into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until lightly browned, about 15 minutes.
Beat 2 eggs, sugar, baking powder, salt, lemon peel and lemon juice with rotary beater until light and foamy.
Pour over hot crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Cool, cut into about 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars. Makes 32 bars.

title: homemade bread
directions: Put water in a large bowl.
Add sugar and yeast.
Let set a few minutes.
Add sifted flour, salt and oil.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, a little at a time until you have a soft dough.
Knead until it isn't sticky.
Turn dough over and grease the top.
Let rise in a warm place until double.
Work down and let rise again.
Make into loaves.
Let rise until light and fluffy.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
This makes 5 loaves.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: In a
bowl, combine corn, thawed broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup crushed crackers, onion, margarine, salt and pepper.

Blend and pour into a 1-quart buttered casserole. Combine 1/2 cup crushed crackers and the melted margarine. Sprinkle over top. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated through and browned on top.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix milk, egg and oil.
Add milk mixture to the cornmeal mixture.
Pour into greased, hot iron skillet.
Bake at 425° about 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sauteed cauliflower
directions: Undercook cauliflower florets.
Heat butter and oil.
Add and cook garlic for 2 minutes.
Remove garlic.
Saute florets until they are well coated.
Cover and cook several minutes longer. Season with salt and paprika.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel and core apples; cover 1/4 of apples with water; add sugar.
Cook until soft.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak crumbs in milk and 1/2 cup catsup until soft.
Add eggs, onion, celery, seasonings and meat.
Mix well and bake 30 minutes. Mix together 4 tablespoons brown sugar, 1/4 cup catsup and dry mustard. Cover meat loaf with this mixture.
Bake 60 minutes longer.

title: dream bars
directions: Beat eggs until light and add sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat well with mixer.
Add nuts and coconut.
Pour over first mixture and bake again about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: burnt sugar fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt and brown 1/2 cup sugar until it forms a dark golden syrup.
Remove from heat.
Let cool a few minutes. Add hot water.
Very slowly stir in rest of sugar, cream, corn syrup and salt.
Cook without stirring to soft ball stage (238° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts; cool slightly, then beat until mixture thickens and begins to lose its gloss.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.
Let stand until firm; cut into squares.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook in saucepan over boiling water until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites for meringue and add 4 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over filling and bake until meringue is done.

title: harvest salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add your own favorite salad dressing.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill and serve.

title: cracker toffee
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Use a cookie sheet with sides or make sides with foil.
Put 40 crackers on foil.
Melt butter. Stir in sugar and drizzle this over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Melt chips and paraffin over hot water; spread chocolate over cooled crackers.
Immediately sprinkle pecans over all.
When cooled, break into pieces.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions until all pink is gone.
Drain and add taco seasoning, water and beans.
Cook until thick. Place broken chips in an 8 x 8 casserole dish, pour the meat mixture over the chips, top with the salsa and grated cheese.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with more tortilla chips and sour cream.
Salsa may also be added on top with the sour cream.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar, and salt in large bowl; cut in 3/4 cup butter thoroughly with a pastry blender until mixture resembles very fine crumbs.
Press mixture evenly into a greased 13 x 9 inch pan, using a piece of plastic wrap to wrap to press crumb mixture firmly in pan.
Bake at 350°
for 17 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Combine brown sugar, corn syrup and 1/2 cup butter in a saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring gently.
Remove from heat.
Stir one-fourth of hot mixture into beaten eggs;
add to remaining hot mixture.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour filling over crust.
Bake at 350° for 34 to 35 minutes or until set.
Cool completely in pan on a wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Yields:
16 bars.

title: honey salad dressing
directions: Combine dry ingredients in small bowl.
Blend with honey.
Add vinegar.
Slowly add oil, beating constantly.
Add salt and paprika to taste.
Easily done with mixer or food processor. Makes two cups.
Really good with summer fruit.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix beaten eggs, herb stuffing, squash, onion, salt and pepper.
Add melted butter.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
This has a seafood taste.
Serves 6.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large pan or Dutch oven (amount of ingredients vary to taste).
Stir over medium heat. Let simmer 1 1/2 hours, check frequently.
Serves 8 to 12.
Even better the next day.

title: pistachio pudding torte
directions: Mix ingredients; press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° until light brown.
Cool completely.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Cream the shortening. Gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy and light.
Add dry mixture alternately with sour milk, mixing well after each addition. Add vanilla and mix until well blended. Combine remaining 2 tablespoons sugar with cinnamon in another bowl.
Spoon half the batter into lightly greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle with half of the sugar/cinnamon mixture. Add remaining batter and sprinkle with remaining sugar/cinnamon mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to
50 minutes or until done.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Brown onion in butter; add tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer
until thick.
Add peppers.
Cook 5 minutes. Just before
serving,
heat
sauce
and
stir
in cheese until melted. Serve with crackers or large chips.

title: cathy's poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken; take off bone and place in baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream together; pour over chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers over top and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with poppy seed (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pastry pie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Mix the flour and salt in a bowl. Combine the syrup and milk, adding this to the flour mixture. Stir with a fork until thoroughly mixed.
Do not overwork the dough.
Shape this mixture into a ball and place it between 2 pieces of wax paper that have been dusted with flour.
Roll the pastry into a circle large enough to fit in a 9-inch pie pan. Spray pan with nonfat cooking spray.
Arrange crust in pan.
Cut off the edges that hang over.
Prick the bottom with a fork.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool before adding filling.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 4 greased pans.
Cook until done at 350°.
Makes 2 two-layer cakes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shell.	Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Drain, reserving 1/4 c. bacon grease. Add crumbled bacon. Combine sugar and flour; add to skillet along with vinegar, water, salt and mustard.
Add onion and celery.

Cook stirring constantly until mixture thickens. In a bowl combine peeled potatoes, carrots and parsley. Pour sauce over and stir gently to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Serve hot or cold. Good both ways.

title: fragrance of christmas
directions: Simmer in open pan on stove during the holidays.
Makes a wonderful holiday aroma.

title: s'more gorp
directions: In a medium paper sack or a large plastic bag, combine the cereal, marshmallows, peanuts, chocolate pieces and raisins. Close bag and shake well.
Store the mixture in a closed plastic bag or a tightly covered container.
Makes 5 cups.
Kids love s'mores!

title: quiche
directions: Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie with maple cream topping
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Heat syrup, margarine and sugar in a 2-quart saucepan to a gentle boil, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool slightly.

title: hot swiss chicken salad sandwiches(8 sandwiches)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except buns.
Fill each bun with 1/4 cup mixture.
Place 4 sandwiches on plastic rack.
Heat on High for 45 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes or until heated through.
Heat 1 sandwich 15 to 30 seconds; two sandwiches 30 to 60 seconds.

title: zola's slush punch
directions: Melt sugar in boiling water (to make syrup) and let cool.
In large bowl, combine syrup and all ingredients except soda pop. Mix well and freeze.
(Ziploc freezer bags work well.)
When ready to serve, place frozen mixture in punch bowl and pour strawberry soda pop over to break it up.
Will be ready to serve in 20 to 30 minutes.
Drowns 25, serves 30 to 50.

title: loaves and fishes
directions: In saucepan, place soup and cream cheese and stir gently over low heat until cream cheese softens.
Add Ortega salsa and cook another 10 minutes.
Hollow out bread; add crab and mushrooms.
Add contents of saucepan.
Stir gently, replace top of bread and heat in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and then chop into small pieces. Mix chicken, sour cream and mushroom soup. Spread mixture in casserole dish. Crush Ritz crackers and mix with melted butter. Top chicken mixture with buttered cracker crumbs. Sprinkle top with poppy seeds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: award winning fudge bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 -inch baking dish.
In a large mixer bowl, beat brown sugar, butter and 1/4 cup peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add combined flour, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in oats and mix well.
Set aside 1 cup of oat mixture.
Spread remaining oat mixture into pan.
Use spatula to spread evenly.

title: english walnut broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter; blend in flour and chicken bouillon. Gradually add milk and cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Sprinkle broken English walnuts over broccoli.
Pour thickened sauce over all.
Sprinkle herbed dressing over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pudding cake(microwave)
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons of the cocoa in bowl.
Stir in milk and melted butter.
Spread mixture in 1 or 1 1/2-quart ring mold (microwave-safe).
Sprinkle top with mixture of brown sugar and remaining cocoa.
Pour hot water on top of batter.
Cook on High for 5 minutes.
