Rotate dish and cook on High for 5 minutes more.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
This is best served warm (with whipped cream) or plain.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Make jello according to directions.
Chill until thickened. Slice cake; place in bottom of 9 x 18-inch dish.
Spread strawberries and juice over cake.
Whip gelatin with high speed mixer.
Add whipped topping; continue to whip until frothy.
Pour over cake and strawberries.
Place in refrigerator until congealed.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream both cheeses. Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Form ball and roll in pecans.

title: german kaiserschmarren(egg dish)
directions: Beat yolk.
Add flour and milk gradually while continuing to mix.
Beat egg whites separately until firm.
Fold egg yolk and flour mixture into egg whites.
Add nuts and raisins.
Heat butter in pan on medium heat.
Ladle batter into pan until it covers bottom of pan.
Brown on 1 side, then flip and brown on other side.
Put in serving dish, then sprinkle with sugar.

title: peach dessert
directions: Put peaches (juice and all) in a
9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of peaches.
Drizzle butter over top of cake mix, then sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 25 minutes on bottom rack of oven and 10 minutes on top rack at 350°.
This may be served with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown eggplant in oil.
Transfer to baking dish. Cover with 3 slices cheese. Spread Ricotta evenly over cheese.
In skillet, saute garlic. Quickly add tomato puree.
Heat thoroughly. Spoon over Ricotta.
Cover with remaining cheese slices.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: spinach balls(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion.
Add spinach, cheese, eggs and seasonings.
Mix all well.
Form into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: walnut sticks
directions: Add sugar, flour, salt and vanilla to beaten eggs and mix well.
Add walnuts.
Spread in a greased shallow (9 x 12 1/2-inch) baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into strips and remove from pan while warm.
Makes 24.

title: swedish apple kaka (cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a spring-form pan (or 9-inch round pan).
Top with 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until done.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: shake and bake
directions: Crush bread into fine crumbs.
Mix with rest of ingredients and store in a tight container.

title: very large banana pudding
directions: Mix thoroughly sugar, flour and salt. Add egg yolks and a little of the milk. Mix well. This will be pastry then. Stir in remainder of milk and add margarine. Cook on medium heat until thickened. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Mix well and let it cool. In a large deep casserole dish place vanilla wafers on bottom and slice the bananas over the wafers. Pour the mix over the bananas and continue repeating layers in this order. Beat egg whites until they form a stiff peak. Add 3 Tbsp. Sugar and beat until stiff. Top banana pudding with egg whites. Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: navaho indian cornmeal cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar together.
Mix in egg.
Add dry mixture to creamed mixture. Drop heaping teaspoonful of dough onto ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Flatten mounds slightly with moistened spoon.
Bake 12 minutes or until light brown. Makes 3 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix ingredients together.
Bake in a greased casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place into well-greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: instant russian tea mix
directions: Measure all ingredients into a 1-quart screw-top jar.
Shake gently to thoroughly combine.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar, powdered sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time and vanilla.
Sift flour and measure with other dry ingredients.
Roll into balls, put on pans and mash with glass dipped into sugar.
Bake 9 minutes at 375°.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg, milk and oil.
Mix dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Beat together.
Cook on hot griddle or frypan.

title: smoked sausage, green beans and potato
directions: Peel potatoes and dice.
Put all in pan and boil until done, or put in a crock-pot on low and cook all day long.
Cut your sausage in pieces.

title: lentils and spinach
directions: Boil the lentils in 1 pint (2 cups) water until soft (about 25 minutes).
Fry sliced onion and chopped garlic; add spices.
Stir about 2 minutes.
Add cooked lentils and washed and coarsely chopped spinach.
Stir well.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add salt and lemon juice.

title: cola barbecue chicken
directions: Mix catsup and soda in electric skillet.
Add chicken.
Cover and cook at simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(Turn chicken once during cooking.)
Messy but wonderful.

title: potato chowder
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and garlic in hot oil until potatoes are transparent (not tender), stirring occasionally. Add chicken soup, tomatoes and seasonings. Cover. Simmer until potatoes are tender, about 25 minutes. Add cream. Heat and serve at once. Serves 4.

title: squash relish
directions: Grind all vegetables in a food chopper; add salt.
Let stand overnight and drain.
Blend together all other ingredients.
Add vegetables and let boil for 3 minutes.
Fill jars and seal.

title: peanut pops
directions: Beat egg; blend
in
brown
sugar.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Blend gradually into egg mixture with oil.
Stir in vanilla extract and chopped
peanuts.
Use	a teaspoon to drop onto lightly oiled or greased
baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until done.
Yields 30 appetizers.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and press flat in a large bread pan.
Heat the remaining 4 ingredients in a saucepan, stirring to blend.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down carrot cake
directions: Heat margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
After melted, add sugar.
Spoon pineapple over brown sugar.
Spread evenly.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving platter. Cool completely.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: party time reubens
directions: Spread each bread slice lightly with mustard and 1/2 teaspoon dressing.
Place 1 tablespoon sauerkraut on each; top with beef and cheese slices.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes or until cheese melts.
Can be made ahead and chilled until time to heat and serve.

title: salad dressing
directions: Cook together sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Shake well before using on tossed salads.

title: toffee
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with foil.
Spray foil with baking spray.
Lay crackers in a single layer to cover foil, crackers touching.
In a saucepan, bring butter and brown sugar to a boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture evenly over crackers, spreading to cover them all.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes, being careful not to let sugar mixture burn.
Remove from oven and let stand about 3 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over candy and, as they melt, spread over entire area with a spatula.
Refrigerate 30 to 60 minutes.
Break into pieces to serve.
Yield:
about 1 1/2 pounds candy.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar, nuts, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to batter.
Mix well.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Punch holes in warm cake.
Frost with juice of 1/2 lemon, mixed with powdered sugar.

title: bolitas de queso (cheese balls)
directions: In a small bowl, blend cheese, egg and cornstarch at high speed.
Take mixture by teaspoons, turn into balls, coat with crumbs and deep-fry until golden brown in fat heated to 350°. Remove and drain on absorbent paper.
Serve immediately.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine crabmeat with all ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Shape 4 patties and coat with bread crumbs.
In large skillet, melt butter.
Add crab cakes and brown on both sides.

title: ten layer chocolate cake
directions: Mix well and beat for 5 minutes.
Makes 10 thin layers. Grease and flour bottom of pans or spray with Pam.
Measure same amount of batter into each pan.
Bake at 350° until done (about 10 minutes).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Do not use pumpkin pie filling.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients quickly.
Drop on boiling stew.
Cook covered for 12 minutes.

title: honey of a chicken breast
directions: Rinse chicken under running cold water; drain and pat dry with paper towel.
Season lightly with salt and pepper.
Combine crumbs and herbs.
Brush all sides of chicken with oil; then roll each piece in crumb mixture until coated on all sides.
Spread honey mixture on each piece of chicken and roll into a ball.
Make a cup of foil to hold each piece of chicken.
Place in baking dish.
Pour wine over each piece of chicken.
Then generously cover top of chicken with more honey sauce, about 1 1/2 tablespoons for each piece.
Place in 375° oven and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: no-cook barbecue sauce
directions: In small bowl stir all ingredients until blended.
Brush on meats or poultry, turning frequently, during last 20 minutes of grilling.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Pour into casserole, then top with the crackers mixed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix sausage, biscuit mix, and self-rising flour.
Set aside. Slice green chilies and wrap them around the cheese cubes.
Pat sausage mix around this and roll to resemble egg shape.
Roll in Shake 'n Bake and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: spider cake
directions: Mix cake mix, vanilla pudding, eggs, vegetable oil and oranges together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter and Milnot on medium heat.
Let boil for 5 minutes (from start of boil).
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: stir-fry cashew chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch chunks.
Heat oil in large black skillet.
Saute chicken quickly.
Push aside.
Add vegetables and saute quickly.
Combine ginger, sugar, salt, soy sauce, bouillon, cornstarch and water and add to chicken and vegetable mixture. Cook until thickens.
Add cashews.
Serve over boiled rice and add Chinese noodles for topping.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable-shrimp stir-fry
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet or wok over medium heat. Add snow peas, onions and red pepper. Stir-fry for 2 minutes. Add shrimp. Stir-fry for 2 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender and most of liquid evaporates. Add soy sauce. Serve over rice.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with 2 ham slices.
Wrap bacon strip around each one.
Place rolled chicken breasts in greased casserole.
Sprinkle mushrooms on top.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken bundles and mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 275° for about 3 hours.
Easy, but tastes like a gourmet dish!
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease 12 medium-sized muffin cups. In bowl, blend with fork the egg, sugar, milk and Bisquick. Beat hard 30 seconds. The batter will be lumpy. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Stir together brown sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon. With a teaspoon, sprinkle cinnamon and sugar mixture over
muffin tops. Bake about 15 minutes, until golden brown. Serve hot. (Good with butter.)

title: fudge
directions: Cook milk, sugar and and salt until comes to soft ball stage. Add butter to syrup.
Pour hot syrup over other ingredients; let it sit 6 to 8 hours after it is put in large pan.
Wrap and store in can.

title: bread pudding
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour for 4-inch pan, 45 minutes for 2-inch pan.

title: spanish vegetable soup
directions: In covered blender container, blend all ingredients until smooth.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Serve with additional chopped vegetables.
Makes 4 cups or 4 servings.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package, using 3 cups of cold milk. Fold in whipping cream.
Line bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with graham crackers.
Top with 1/3 pudding mix.
Continue, making 3 layers.
End with graham crackers.
Glaze with recipe following. Place in fridge several hours or overnight.

title: carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly coat a loaf pan with margarine or butter, then dust with flour.
Mix sugar and applesauce in a bowl.
Combine dry ingredients and add to applesauce mixture.
Add carrots, vanilla, and nuts.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Pour into pan and bake for 50 minutes.
Serve with soups, hearty salads, and stews!

title: wedding or party punch
directions: Mix sherbets and stir until mushy.
Add quarts of 7-up and Squirt and stir.
This makes a delicate green foamy punch.
Serves 50.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: One of those mixers (you put it in the dough to mix all the stuff.)
When the dough is soft, take a handful of dough and make a round ball.
Put on cookie pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding according to box directions.
Use both boxes as if just preparing one box.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip to pudding mix.
Layer wafers, then bananas in glass dish.
Pour pudding mixture over layers.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours or overnight. Serve cold.

title: working girl's salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk with electric mixer. Fold in balance of ingredients.
Let set at least 6 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut the broccoli into small pieces.
Break the bacon into pieces and chop onion.
Add bacon, onion and cheese together.
Then mix up dressing and stir into broccoli mixture.

title: lazy gal's delight
directions: Empty half of cake mix into 7 x 12-inch loaf pan.
Spread filling over mix without stirring. Sprinkle remaining mix over the filling.
Pour water over all.
Drizzle butter over the water. Sprinkle with cinnamon (optional).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: sausage wild rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, onion, pepper and celery; drain.
In large bowl, combine sausage, rice and season packet, soup, broth and mushrooms.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13 baker.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hello dollies
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch square pan, melt butter.
Add graham cracker crumbs and mix.
Spread evenly over the bottom of the tin. Sprinkle semi-sweet chocolate bits evenly over graham cracker base. Follow with coconut and walnuts.
Then drizzle one can sweetened condensed milk over top, evenly.
With a fork, distribute this by going through once.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Grease 8 x 10-inch roasting pan with butter.
Place dried beef on bottom of pan.
Wrap chicken breast around block of cheese. Wrap bacon around chicken and put a toothpick through it.
Mix soup, 1/2 can water and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cover tight with foil.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: banana nut salad
directions: Layer chopped peanuts, marshmallows, bananas and Miracle Whip. Then add layers again until all are used.
Be sure to add ground peanuts on top layer of salad.
Refrigerate.

title: christmas confetti
directions: Mix together and serve with crackers.

title: bramborova polevka(potato soup)
directions: *Dried mushrooms should be soaked and drained.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually until smooth.
Add cooled, melted margarine to egg mixture.
Dough will be sticky enough to drop by the spoonful.
Heat pizzelle pan well.
Bake 15 seconds approximately.
Quickly remove from heat and place flat.

title: roast pork loin and red cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (180° C).
Rub the pork loin with oil. Season by sprinkling salt, pepper, paprika and cinnamon over the roast.
Place on a rack in roasting pan.
Bake 2 hours.
While loin is roasting, fry bacon in a large skillet.
Remove; set aside. Drain all the bacon fat; reserve 1/4 cup.
Place cabbage in skillet; saute 3 minutes in reserved bacon fat.
Add the caraway seed, sugar, bacon and sherry.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Place on serving platter.
Slice roast and serve on cabbage.
Garnish with sprigs of parsley and thin celery strips or French-cut green beans.
Serves 8.

title: easy cabbage casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add rice and drain.
In oblong dish, layer cabbage and meat mixture.
Pour tomato soup and water over top. Bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 or 1 1/2 hours.
Just before done, sprinkle cheese on top to melt.

title: sweet party mix
directions: Melt chocolate 2 or 3 minutes in microwave.
Pour over the rest of the ingredients and stir well to coat. Turkey roaster works well.

title: crispy crullers
directions: Add all or enough flour to egg yolks and sour cream to make soft dough.
Add sugar, salt, brandy and vinegar.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out very thin.
Cut into diamond shapes.
Make slit in center and pull one end through slit.
Deep fry until light brown.
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pasta and chicken primavera
directions: In large skillet, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add chicken, onion, garlic and basil; stir frequently.
Cook until chicken turns white.
Add zucchini and carrots; stir frequently. Stir in wine, parsley and red pepper (if you like).
Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes, until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Add the packet of chicken broth, dissolved in 1 cup warm water.
Place cooked spaghetti in large platter, top with sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Toss together and serve.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: aunt miriam's yeast rolls
directions: Put the 7 cups of flour in mixing bowl; make a well in flour. Add 2 cups warm water, oil, salt and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 cup warm water until dissolved; add to the other mixture and mix well.
If too sticky, add 1/2 cup flour.
Mix and knead well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in greased, covered casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: tortilla mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Blend in shortening until texture of corn meal.
Keep in 10-cup sealed container.
Store in cool place.
Keeps 10 to 12 weeks.

title: italian beef
directions: Brown roast or brisket in 2 tablespoons of oil in a large Dutch oven.
Season roast generously over the top with salt, pepper, garlic powder, rosemary and oregano.
Pour chicken broth over the seasoned meat.
Cover and bake in a slow oven at 300°, basting frequently, until very tender, about 4 to 5 hours.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese, margarine and vanilla. Beat all together and spread on cake.
Roll up and chill.

title: strawberry citrus sparkler
directions: In blender, combine orange juice, lemon juice and strawberries and ice and sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into 4 (10 ounce) glasses.
Fill slowly with soda.
Top with a scoop of ice cream. Garnish with strawberries, if desired.

title: sweet potato and cranberry casserole
directions: Boil sweet potatoes for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool, peel and slice them into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cranberry sauce, sherry, brown sugar and nutmeg in saucepan.
Add water to cornstarch and mix well.
Add to saucepan; bring to a boil and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in butter until melted.
Pour sauce over potatoes and bake uncovered for 25 minutes.
Serves 8 people.

title: chicken d'artichoke
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichokes and arrange in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Spread chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Toss bread cubes in melted butter and pour over cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon cabbage slaw
directions: Combine jello with hot water.
Add sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and salt.
Mix vegetables and gelatin.
Pour 1/2 cup salad oil over all.
Mix.
Chill for 1 hour or more.
Keeps well.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain peaches, saving 1/3 cup of syrup. Put peaches and syrup in a 1-quart casserole.
Mix flour, sugar and egg, making a crumbly mixture.
Sprinkle mixture over peaches and drizzle melted margarine over the top.
Bake for 45 minutes until top is brown.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix in flour when onions are browned. Meanwhile, combine and heat beef broth, bay leaf and pepper.
Add onions and cook for 30 minutes.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Cut stew beef into smallish pieces, having trimmed fat from meat.
Use small new potatoes, unpeeled or cut peeled potatoes into golf ball sized pieces.
Use small onions or quarter 2 large ones.
Peel and cut carrots into 2-inch chunks.
Layer, without mixing together, the beef, potatoes, onions and carrots.
Add peas and tomato soup.
Use a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Uncover 10 minutes.
Add wine.
Stir and serve.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and celery.
Add salt and pepper.
Put in roaster and add mushroom soup and chicken soup, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce, rice and water.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° to 375°, uncovered.
Add more water, if necessary, during baking time, and stir several times.
Add chow mein noodles on top the last 15 minutes.

title: corn dish
directions: Melt butter and flour together, then add corn, whipping cream, salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Stir 2 or 3 times while baking.

title: special breakfast drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and process on high speed until smooth.
Makes 1 serving.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place lemon, salt, rosemary, oregano and red pepper.
Put shrimp over this and sprinkle lightly with salt and heavy with pepper.
In a saucepan over medium heat, melt butter and shortening.
Add barbecue spice and garlic.
Pour over shrimp and bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, depending on size of shrimp.
Serve with French bread.
Bread dipped in juice is great.
Serve with green salad.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter together.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Frost cool cake.

title: rhubarb souffle pie
directions: Mix the sugar and cut rhubarb.
Separate the eggs.
Add a dash of salt to beaten egg yolks and add to the rhubarb.
Stir well.
Beat the egg whites and gradually add the 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Egg whites should be stiff.
Fold into rhubarb mixture. Pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn heat down to 300° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients, using only 1 package of wafer meat which has been chopped.
Spoon onto a plate in a mound or make a log. Slice remaining meat in squares and cover mound or log.
Needs to be made a day or several hours before serving.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together sugar, butter and eggs until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture with the buttermilk.
Beat until blended.
Stir in nuts, cherries and vanilla.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Cook macaroni. Mix with hamburger and soups. Add salt, pepper and garlic salt. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients in a thin dish. Wash tomatoes and slice to
desired thickness. Dip tomatoes in the eggs, then in flour mixture.
Fry
in hot shortening until brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Ready to eat.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix well all ingredients. Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Defrost loaves 2 minutes in microwave.
Roll each one out in the largest, flattest rectangle possible.
Brush with melted butter; leave 1/2 inch along long edge unbuttered.
Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar.
Roll up and seal (long tube shape).
Cut each into 14 pieces.
Place on roasting pan which has been sprinkled with lots of pecan pieces.
Leave space to rise (7 pieces x 4 pieces).

title: vivian's baked beans
directions: Fry bacon; let drain.
Combine all other ingredients in a 9 x 10-inch baking dish.
Crumble bacon up and add to ingredients. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheesy carrots
directions: In a bowl, combine the carrots, soup and cheese.
Transfer to a greased 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 10 minutes; stir.
Toss bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over the top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until carrots are tender and mixture is bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan the chopped nuts and coconut.
Pour the prepared cake mix with the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour over the above.
Bake about 45 minutes at 325°.

title: orange pear salad
directions: Drain pears; reserve juice. Place pear juice in a saucepan and bring to a boil; then add gelatin and stir until dissolved. Refrigerate mixture until partially set. Blend pears and cream cheese into mixture; add lemon juice, whipping cream and gelatin mixture. Blend well. Pour in mold and refrigerate until firm. Top with Cool Whip.

title: southern indiana pork barbecue sauce
directions: Put all ingredients into saucepan.
Heat until oleo is dissolved.
Mix ingredients; brush on pork chops.
Broil over medium charcoal fire.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: Drain mushrooms, reserving 1/4 cup of liquid.
Put mushrooms with beans in a heavy pot and add oil, onion, mushroom liquid, salt and sugar.
Turn heat low and cook until tender.
Add cream. Heat well and serve.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
Fry in iron skillet to golden brown in oil.

title: peanut butter fudge(3 minutes)
directions: Put all ingredients except peanut butter and vanilla in heavy saucepan, boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 9-inch pan.
Cool before cutting.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Cut up cucumbers in rings.
Cut up onions in rings.
Cut up peppers and garlic.
Add salt and cover with ice and let stand for 3 hours.
Then rinse good with cold water.
Mix all ingredients together and add cucumbers and bring to a rolling boil.
Put in jars quickly.
Do not overcook!

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll rolls and spread on large Pam sprayed cookie sheet. Pinch together into a single piece and bake 10 minutes at 350° or until light brown on top.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing and beat together until blended.
Add dash of garlic. Spread on top of baked cooled rolls.
Sprinkle on carrots, cauliflower, broccoli and green pepper.
Then sprinkle cheese on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: butterscotch chinese noodle cookies
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter in large bowl in microwave.
When melted, mix in noodles.
Take out by tablespoonfuls and put on wax paper to dry.

title: creamed carrots with oregano
directions: Boil the carrots in salted water about 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Peel the carrots but leave them whole. Keep warm.
In skillet, melt the butter.
Add the flour and cook for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.
Gradually blend in the cream, whisking continually.
Stir a little of the cream mixture into the egg yolk.
Add egg yolk to creme mixture, stirring well.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Add oregano and salt to taste.
Place carrots in a serving dish.
Pour into sauce.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Clean shrimp; drain well on paper towels.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish in oven. Add salt, garlic and 1 tablespoon parsley; mix well.
Arrange shrimp in single layer in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp.
Sprinkle with lemon peel, lemon juice and remaining parsley.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or just until tender.
Arrange shrimp on heated serving platter.
Pour garlic butter over all.
Serve over rice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Add to sausage and Bisquick.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls or patties.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: salad bowl puff
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil.
Stir in flour and salt.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 30 seconds.
Remove from heat; cool 10 minutes.
Beat in eggs all at once.
Continue to beat until smooth.
Spread dough evenly in pie plate, building up edge slightly.
Bake until puffed and dry in center, 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Just before serving, fill with ham salad or tuna filling.
Cut into wedges.

title: orange pineapple sherbet
directions: Mix together and freeze in an ice cream freezer.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Wash fruit and put in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all the remaining ingredients and put over top of fruit.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together and sprinkle over batter.
Add remaining batter and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
After baking, glaze cake with powdered sugar and milk mixture.

title: italian grilled chicken
directions: Remove excess fat from breasts.
Put in lidded bowl.
Add enough salad dressing to cover chicken.
Marinate for 2 to 6 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Grill over hot charcoal for 5 minutes each side.

title: three bean cassoulet(high fiber)
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart slow cooker.
Cover.
Cook on high setting 30 minutes. Reduce to low setting.
Cook 5 to 6 hours or until vegetables are tender. Remove bay leaf.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: chocolate kahlua heath bar trifle
directions: Bake chocolate cake; let stand, covered, overnight.
Crumble cake and shake Kahlua over it.
Let soak in.
Place 1/2 Kahlua cake in a trifle bowl.
Spread 1/2 chocolate pudding on top of cake.
Spread 1/2 of whipped heavy cream on top of pudding and sprinkle with 1/2 of Heath bars.
Repeat layering again cake, pudding, heavy cream and Heath bars.

title: cauliflower-pea salad
directions: In large bowl, combine cauliflower, peas, celery and onion. Mix mayonnaise, Ranch mix and milk and pour over vegetables. Better if made a day ahead.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add celery, onions and pepper.
Cook until tender, but not brown; then add soup.
Cook macaroni and drain. Add to meat along with other ingredients.
Bake 1 hour on 300°. Makes 1 large or 2 small casseroles.

title: raspberry coconut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package for two 9-inch round cake layers, adding 2/3 cup of the coconut to batter.
Mix jam and 1 cup coconut.
Spread between cake layers.
Frost top and sides of cake with whipped topping.
Press remaining coconut on top and sides.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves 12.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, dump in undrained pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Smooth out to fill pan.
Next, spread dry cake mix over pineapple-cherry mixture.
Sprinkle nuts on next. Dot with 1 to 2 sticks oleo.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until brown.

title: mud pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a round pan, 8 x 1 1/2-inches or a pie plate, 8 x 1 1/4-inches, with shortening.
Mix granulated sugar, margarine, vanilla, salt, eggs and flour in a medium bowl with spoon; stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Immediately prick holes in pie with toothpick; spread fudge sauce over top.
Cool completely.
Beat whipping cream and powdered sugar in a small bowl until stiff; spread over fudge sauce.
Drizzle with additional fudge sauce if you like.
Store pie in refrigerator.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy yogurt bread
directions: Gently stir water, yeast and honey together to dissolve.
Let the mixture sit for 5 minutes.
Add the salt and yogurt, mixing thoroughly.
Gradually stir in the flour with a heavy spoon.
Turn out on floured board and knead for 5 minutes.
Slice the dough in two and place in 2 greased loaf pans.
Let rise about 45 minutes and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oven-fried pork chops
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine baking mix with paprika, seasoned salt and pepper on waxed paper.
Coat pork chops with mixture.
Arrange in a prepared baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes.
Turn chops over.
Bake for 15 minutes longer.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: texas chili
directions: Soak beans in water all afternoon.
Put in slow cooker on low and simmer all night with water covering beans.
In the morning, brown in skillet the meat and chili powder.
Add directly to beans without browning.
First, add onion, pepper and celery.
Then add chili meat and stir.
Two hours before serving meal, add 1 can tomato soup and stir until blended.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, add sugar gradually and cream well with wooden spoon.
Add milk gradually to sugar mixture, then the well beaten egg and vanilla.
Sift in the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough (if needed) and turn out on a floured board.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut and place on buttered pans and bake in a hot oven (350°) until slightly brown.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan; line with waxed paper. Grease and flour paper. Sprinkle tea towel with powdered sugar. Combine flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and salt in a small bowl. Beat eggs and sugar in a large bowl until thick. Beat in pumpkin. Stir in flour mixture. Spread evenly into prepared pan. Sprinkle with nuts, if desired. Bake for 13 to 15 minutes or until top of cake springs back when touched. Immediately loosen and turn cake onto prepared towel. Carefully peel off paper. Roll up cake and towel, starting with narrow end. Cool on wire rack.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Lightly sprinkle and rub seasoning salt onto both sides of meat.
Mix both sauces together and coat meat thickly.
Place slab on broiler/drain pan and broil for 15 to 20 minutes or until done. Turn frequently.

title: easy chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of Swiss cheese on each chicken breast.
Top with another chicken breast and secure with toothpicks, if desired.
Top with the mushroom soup and sour cream, mixed together.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: bread and butter pickles(dietetic)
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and garlic in large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover with ice cubes.
Let stand overnight.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients, except liquid artificial sweetener.
Add cucumber mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and boil gently for 2 minutes.
Stir in sweetener.
Remove garlic clove.
Spoon into sterile jars.
Seal.
Yield: 5 cups. Exchanges: 1/2 cup = 1 vegetable and contains 28 calories.

title: summer salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and enjoy with tortilla chips or use in your favorite Mexican recipe.
Store in refrigerator.

title: graham cracker-cheese strawberry dessert
directions: Mix and press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: super punch
directions: Mix first three ingredients together in a punch bowl.
Place the sherbet in the middle of the bowl and pour dippers of punch over the sherbet, so the punch will be chilled.
Serve with a little sherbet in each cup.

title: ham stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons oleo.
Add ham, mushrooms and soup.
Stir until heated through; stir in sour cream and heat carefully.
Do not boil.
Cook noodles and drain; add 2 tablespoons oleo and poppy seed.
Serve ham over noodles.

title: raspberry cloud
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened, 15 minutes.
Puree 1 cup raspberries in blender; strain through sieve and discard seeds; add yogurt.
Stir yogurt mixture into gelatin and refrigerate.
Beat egg whites and salt until frothy; gradually beat in sugar, beating until stiff but not dry.
Fold egg whites into gelatin; do not stir vigorously.
Spoon into dessert dishes; top with raspberries and whipped topping.

title: seafood chowder
directions: In saucepan cook celery and garlic in butter until celery is tender.
Add soup, water and seafood.
Heat and stir.
Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Slice apples to 2/3 full in 9-inch pie pan.
Mix other ingredients and spread over apples.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
In a double boiler or thick pot, melt chocolate. Fold into cream cheese mixture with pecans.
Spread into a buttered pan. Chill and cut into squares.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Cut tips off chicken wings; separate at joints.

title: chocolate chip-cream cheese squares
directions: Cream first four ingredients together.
Slice 1 package cookie dough and place in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top.
Slice other roll of cookie dough and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.
Enjoy!

Seal the pan with foil. Cook

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion soup mix and Blue cheese dressing. Roll into a ball.
Roll ball into chopped walnuts.
Refrigerate before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, soda, cinnamon, Wesson oil, eggs and carrots and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.
Cool before frosting.
Cream margarine and cheese together.
Add sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Use between layers on top and sides of cake.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat well at medium speed.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Beat well after each one.
Combine buttermilk and soda.
Stir until dissolved.
Add flour; alternate buttermilk mixture, ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla; add 1 cup walnuts and coconut.
Stir well.
Beat egg whites at room temperature and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake for 22 to 25 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool completely.

title: alpine chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Mix thoroughly by hand or with spoon.
Place into lightly-greased dish.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.
Suggest serving with asparagus, salad or both.

title: apple puffed pancake
directions: In blender or mixer bowl, mix eggs, milk, flour, sugar, vanilla, salt and cinnamon until well blended.
Batter will be lumpy.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven.
Add apple slices to pan (should sizzle).
Return to oven until butter sizzles.
Do not let brown.
Remove dish from oven and immediately pour batter over apples.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake in middle of 425° oven for 20 minutes until puffed and brown.
Serve immediately.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine brown sugar and margarine in bottom of cake pan.
Top with pineapple slices.
Beat egg yolks until thick, add sugar, add baking powder, salt and flour.
Pour over slices.
Top with beaten egg whites.
Bake until done.
Top with whipped cream.

title: pancite
directions: Mix together soy sauce, lemon juice and garlic; set aside. Steam vegetables.
Simmer meat, poultry or pork in 1 cup water until thoroughly cooked.
Save broth.
Prepare rice noodles or linguini as directed.

title: florida fruit punch
directions: Garnishes (optional):
Orange and carambola slices and maraschino cherries.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken with 2 strips of bacon.
Cover bottom of greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish with chipped beef.
Arrange chicken on chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Serves 4.

Makes about 6 dozen rolls and freezes well.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme. Beat until thick.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: pate mousse with bacon and walnuts
directions: One day before serving, fry the diced bacon in a medium skillet until crisp.
Remove from the pan with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Saute the livers in the hot bacon fat over medium-high heat until brown on the outside, but still pink inside, 4 or 5 minutes.
Remove from the pan and reserve.
Pour the brandy into the skillet over medium heat and stir, scraping loose browned bits on the bottom of the pan.
Add the cream and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer until reduced to about 1 cup.
Process the livers, onion and reduced cream in a food processor fitted with a steel blade until smooth.
Add the mayonnaise, thyme, nutmeg, salt to taste and lots of pepper. Process until smooth.
Add the diced bacon, walnuts and 3 tablespoons parsley and process just until blended.
Transfer the liver mixture to a crock-pot or decorative serving dish and refrigerate, covered, overnight to allow the flavors to blend.

title: crumb topping
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter. Sprinkle atop pie.

title: marbleized squares
directions: Beat butter until light and add white and brown sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla until thoroughly mixed.
